title: brandied fruit
directions: Open cans, drain fruits, retaining about 1/2 cup to make syrup with brandy and brown sugar.
Arrange fruit with pineapple on bottom in large baking dish.
Drizzle brandy/fruit/brown sugar mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° until fruit is heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: oyster patties
directions: Melt butter and add flour.
When smooth, add all other ingredients, except oysters.
Simmer about 5 minutes.

title: herb stuffed mushrooms
directions: Process 3/4 pound mushrooms, salt, pepper, basil, parsley and onions in a food processor or blend until thick and smooth.
Layer 1/2 cup of the mushroom mixture in bottom of a baking dish.

title: lazy betty cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and pour filling in.
Sprinkle unmixed package of cake mix over filling.
Sprinkle nuts over this.
Melt margarine and drizzle over entire top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in hot skillet on both sides until lightly browned. Place ribs in shallow baking dish.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over ribs and cover dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Do not turn ribs.
Add water if necessary.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Place sugar, butter, and corn syrup in small pan and cook until syrupy.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Slice French bread 3/4 inches thick and arrange in pan over syrup mixture.
Beat together eggs, milk, and vanilla flavoring.
Pour over bread.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350-375° for 40-45 minutes.
This makes its own syrup, but it can also be served with additional maple syrup.

title: layered salad
directions: Make in layers and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours before serving. Toss and serve.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put margarine, water, cooking oil and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Put sugar and flour in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs.
Put the soda in the sour milk and dissolve it.
Put hot mixture in the bowl and mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a greased jelly roll pan.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Keep adding buttermilk until a little thicker than cornbread.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil; cook until brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Prepare macaroni according to package instructions.
Drain macaroni and layer half of it in bottom of dish.
Top with half the cheese and half of onion.
Repeat layers.
Combine the egg, evaporated milk and salt in mixing bowl.
Pour it over the macaroni.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: aggie punch
directions: Freeze juices in their cans.
One hour before serving, set out frozen cans.
When ready to serve, mix juices with 7-Up.
No ice needed.
Yield:
30 servings.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water until dissolved.
Add 1 cup ice water.
Stir.
Add pineapple with 1 cup of the pineapple juice.
Stir in walnuts and add sour cream.
Stir until ingredients are dissolved and mixed well.
Refrigerate until set.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Beat eggs lightly; mix with oil and yeast.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix 1/2 of flour, then add the rest. Refrigerate overnight in a large oiled bowl, covered with a damp cloth.
Knead well.
Make 2 large loaves; let rise in a warm place for about 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until golden and sounds hollow when tapped, about 20 minutes.

title: southern-style brisket sauce
directions: Cut fat into 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat in a large skillet until melted.
Pour 1 cup of fat in saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat until thick, about 1 hour.

title: swirl coffee cake(serves 20.  yummy!!!)
directions: Spread in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Put crumb mixture on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in 1 1/2-quarts water.
Cool and debone.
Saute pepper and onion in oleo.
Add mushrooms to onions and pepper and heat until warm.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, English peas and olives. Cook spaghetti in broth from chicken.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add everything else and mix well.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes over 16 cups.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler.
Add milk.
Stir until well blended.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Cool and add vanilla.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cover bottom of 9 x 13 pan with dry Minute rice (just cover bottom). Cover dry rice with the cooked hamburger. Drain most of water from vegetables. Spread vegetables over burger. Pour chicken and rice soup over top of vegetables. Spread mushroom soup in thin layer to cover complete pan. Cook in oven 40 minutes or until bubbles in center.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Chill and serve over an ice ring in a punch bowl.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: hello dollies or layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter; sprinkle coconut over crumbs.
Layer chocolate bits, butterscotch pieces and nuts over crumbs.
Pour condensed milk over nuts.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: meat n tater pie
directions: Measure corn flakes, then crush to 2 cups.
Measure 1/2 cup of the crushed corn flakes, milk, salt, pepper and mustard into mixing bowl; beat well.
Stir in ground beef.
Place in 9-inch pie pan.
Set aside.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for ginger ale and chill. Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: aram sandwiches
directions: Hold lavash one at a time under cold running water until thoroughly moistened.
Place between two dish towels and gently roll up.
Set aside.

title: caesar salad
directions: Shake in jar and refrigerate.

title: cranberry cheese pie(10-inch pie plate)
directions: Chill pastry for firmness.
Spread cranberry sauce all over pastry.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cranberry in pie plate.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: quick tuna pie
directions: Mix all canned ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat in oven until mixture bubbles.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Roll out dough.
Cover casserole with biscuit dough and bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: chicken in broccoli sauce
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in a well greased skillet.
Mix together broccoli soup and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken; cover and simmer on top of stove until chicken is tender.
Turn chicken halfway through cooking time.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Stew the chicken with your favorite seasonings and cool, reserving 2 cups of the broth.
Remove chicken from bone and tear in pieces.
Place in shallow 3-quart (9 x 13-inch) baking dish. Combine soups and 1 cup broth and pour over chicken.
Mix margarine or butter and remaining broth; stir in stuffing and spoon over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: lemon-chicken pasta
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add oil. Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add garlic; saute 15 seconds.
Add chicken; saute 1 minute.
Add peas and carrot; saute 1 minute.
Remove from skillet; set aside.

title: aunt mae's rice salad
directions: Cook the rice and cool.
Mix all ingredients.
Top with cherries.

title: chocolate cream cake (1935)(a robin hood pre-sifted flour recipe)
directions: Pour boiling water over chocolate squares in bowl.
Let stand until cool.
Cream butter and vanilla.
Add brown sugar and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Spoon flour (not sifted) into dry measuring cup.
Level off and pour measured flour onto a square of waxed paper.
Add soda and salt to flour (not sifted) and stir to blend.
Stir blended ingredients into creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Blend in sour cream and chocolate-water mixture.

title: peach cake pie
directions: Mix peaches, water and flour in a bowl.
Pour into buttered, greased flat Pyrex dish.
Spread dry cake mix over ingredients. Place slices of butter over cake mix evenly.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplants, drain, mash and mix with the 2 well beaten eggs.
Add chopped onion, soup, salt and pepper.
Layer all ingredients with cracker crumbs and grated cheese.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Mix ingredients until evenly distributed and serve with corn chips.

title: strawberry peach cooler
directions: Combine strawberries and peaches in a bowl; sprinkle with sugar.
Stir and let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. Pour fruit into a punch bowl.
Gently pour in wine and water.
Add ice.

title: orange tidbit cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together.
Add eggs and mix well. Continue adding and mixing until all is mixed together.
Cool in refrigerator about 1 hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Separate egg and beat white until stiff.
Mix flour, sugar, and milk with beater.
Gently fold in egg white with spoon.
Drop 3 to 4 tablespoon batter onto oiled griddle for each pancake. Makes about 4 medium-sized pancakes.

title: peanut butter, corn flake cookies
directions: Put sugar and syrup in container.
Let come to a boil (just a boil), stirring continuously.
Add peanut butter to syrup mixture and stir until smooth.
Pour this over corn flakes and work quickly, blending thoroughly, to coat flakes.
Pour out into greased pan. Cut while warm. Makes about 100.

title: charlotte's old fashioned wilted lettuce
directions: In a small bowl, beat eggs, milk, vinegar, salt and pepper until smooth.
Set aside.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon to paper towel to drain.

title: baked beans
directions: Spray deep casserole bowl with Pam.
Stir all ingredients together in casserole bowl.
Top with 8 oz. can drained peaches and 5 oz. can of Vienna sausage (optional).
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: rotel chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender. Save 1 1/2 to 2 cups of broth. Chop up chicken. Saute onions in 1 stick of butter.
Add Velveeta, broth, Ro-Tel, Worcestershire sauce and chicken. Simmer for a few minutes. Cook vermicelli and drain. Add to chicken mixture. Add peas and mushrooms.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix sausage, Bisquick and shredded cheese together and form into 1-inch balls.
Place sausage balls on cookie sheet or flat pan with raised edges.
Cook 20 minutes at 325° on one side, turn over and cook until done.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Stir the dry ingredients together and add to the cream mixture.
Stir in chopped apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While still warm, top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, bananas and nuts.
Mix soda and flour with other mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn oven back to 275° and bake for 20 minutes.
Stick toothpick in center. If it comes out clean, it is done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Broil chicken until tender, remove meat from bones and cut into bite-size pieces. Cook celery, onion, and bell pepper in margarine until tender. Add mushroom, tomato soup, chicken broth, chili powder, tobasco sauce, and salt to taste. Mix with cooked deboned chicken and spaghetti; cooked and drained. Put into a 11x15 in. pan, sprinkle with grated cheese and cook at 350° until bubbly - about 30 minutes.
Serves 15-20.

title: diane's noodle kugel (or bubies kugel)
directions: Make pie crust or use 3 boxes of mix.
Butter high sided round pan and line with dough in one piece (roll dough thin but flexible enough to line pan).
Fix any breaks in dough.

title: spinach cheese casserole
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Cook carrots and onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Stir in soup, spinach, rice and milk.
Pour mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top and serve.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, eggs and dates.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture leaves sides of pan, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rice cereal, walnuts and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Let cool; shape into rolls about 3-inches long.
Roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and pulp.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In oven-proof 10-inch skillet melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth and milk. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Add chicken, onion, peas and carrots. Simmer until hot and bubbly. Separate biscuits and arrange over hot chicken mixture. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients, using only 1/2 the sauce.
Mix remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Pour over meat loaf; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg, vanilla and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Add oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: tijuana casserole(low-fat)
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet.
(Wash meat by placing in colander under hot top water after browning.)
Return to skillet, add all other ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
Heat until hot.

title: mississippi corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix well and knead.
Place in large greased bowl and let raise until double in bulk.
Roll dough out with rolling pin.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except for potato chips.
Add chips on top of mixture before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: plant food
directions: Mix ingredients together in a gallon jar or jug.
Fill with warm water.
Mixture may foam so add water slowly.
Water plants regularly with solution as needed.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs in a bowl until blended (it will be sticky).
With floured hands, roll level tablespoon into balls.
Place 1 1/4-inches apart
on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until cookies look crackled.
Remove from oven and press chocolate kiss in center of cookie.
Put back in oven for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove to wire racks.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine cabbage, apples, raisins, nuts and enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add pumpkin, eggs and water. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Add nuts and blend well.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: garlic-lime chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate chicken for 1 hour, turning occasionally.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil until clear.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook at a low temperature until warm all the way through.

title: nutmeg cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla extract.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pans on rack 10 minutes.
Turn out of pans onto rack and cool completely.

title: heath bars
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil, lightly buttered.
Melt butter (2 sticks) in brown sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring continually.
Line buttered pan with saltines.
Pour cooked mixture over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 9 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Spread.

title: egg nog punch(good for holidays!)
directions: In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat 6 egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar until stiff peaks form.
In small bowl with mixer at medium-low speed, beat the 6 egg yolks and 1/2 cup Karo syrup about 5 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Add 1/2 pint half and half cream.
Beat until well mixed.
Fold into egg white mixture.
If desired, stir in 1/4 cup dark or light rum.
Cover and refrigerate.
Place 1 pint vanilla ice cream in punch bowl.
Pour egg nog mixture over ice cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 24 half-cup servings.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sugar.
Set aside and let congeal lightly.
Add rice, cheese and pineapple.
Fold in nuts and whipped Dream Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken-broccoli au gratin
directions: In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup and milk. Arrange chicken in soup mixture, turning to coat.

title: pizza bread
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Cut bread lengthwise and spread with topping.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chops with tomatoes
directions: Rinse beans.
Cook in water with a little salt for about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Reserve juices.
Lightly grease an ovenproof plate.
Place beans on plate.
Rinse tomatoes.
Cut into wedges. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: sunshine salad(an ebert family favorite)
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Pour over jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple, pineapple juice plus water, carrots, pecans, salt and lemon juice.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch container. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; beat until well blended.
In a separate bowl, mix the next 5 ingredients.
Add this to first mixture; beat well.
Add zucchini; mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for glass and at 350° for metal, for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mango salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling liquid. Combine mangos and cream cheese in blender and blend until creamy. Add to Jell-O and stir in lime juice and rind.
Pour into a greased mold and chill overnight.	Unmold and serve on bed of shredded lettuce. Garnish with kiwi and/or strawberries. Makes a very pretty dish for luncheon.

title: brandy balls
directions: Combine the crushed wafers, nutmeats, powdered sugar, corn syrup, cocoa and brandy in a mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into firm balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Roll in powdered sugar. Store in a tightly closed container until served.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables, gravy, salt and pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with egg slices.

title: spanish rice
directions: In large skillet fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan. Saute onion in 3 tablespoons bacon grease.
Add green pepper and hamburg.
Cook until nearly done.
Add tomatoes and simmer until well done.
Add crumbled bacon.
Combine with rice.
Spoon into Pam sprayed casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Serves about 8.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, cinnamon, soda, flour and pumpkin.
Pour into shallow greased and sugar sprinkled pan (jelly roll type). Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto towel that has been dusted with confectioners sugar.

title: arabian macaroons(my christmas cookies)
directions: Mix the first
ingredients well, then add the beaten egg and vanilla; blend.
Let stand 5 minutes, then drop from a teaspoon onto greased
baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown at
Remove
at	once
from
baking
sheet. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: raggedy ann salad
directions: On a plate, arrange cottage cheese for head, raisins for eyes, cherry half for mouth and grated cheese for hair.
Use celery sticks for arms and green olives for hands.
Use peach half for the body and a lettuce leaf for the skirt.
Use celery sticks for legs and black olives for shoes.
That's all there is to it!

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Stir in flour; cook until bubbly.
Add water and chicken flavor. Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
In large pan, combine 1 cup sauce with chicken, 1 cup cheese, chilies, pimentos, cumin and chili powder.
Fill tortillas with meat mixture and roll up.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon remaining sauce over top.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Delicious!

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the sugar, eggs (slightly beaten), vinegar, vanilla, salt, raisins, coconut and pecans.
Mix in the order given.
Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 300° and bake for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: chocolate filled snowballs
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; blend well.
Chill dough.
Take foil off Kisses; shape dough around Kisses.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown (do not overbake).
Roll in powdered sugar while warm; repeat when cooled.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 15 minutes or until tender; drain and mash. Add butter and cream cheese; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Stir in 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and next 6 ingredients; spoon into lightly buttered 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: ginger cream cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar, add egg, molasses and water.
Slowly mix in remaining dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with cream cheese icing to which 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg has been added.

title: amaretto
directions: Boil sugar and water for 50 minutes with lid on pot.
Add Karo and stir; let cool.
Add vodka and extracts.
Stir.
Store for at least 2 weeks or more.

title: bake-rite pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of loaf pans.
Mix Bake-Rite and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix in chopped nuts and raisins.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool completely before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans, 3 loaves in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans.

title: delicious pound cake
directions: Cream together	butter	and
sugar.
Add
eggs one at a time. Beat thoroughly after each addition.
Sift flour before measuring and add a pinch of salt.
Alternate adding cream and flour, beating
all
the
time.
Add
almond
flavoring.
Use greased tube pan which has been sprinkled with flour.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door.

title: vanilla frozen yogurt
directions: Scald evaporated milk over low heat to avoid "skinning". Stir.
Add sugar, salt and softened gelatin.
Stir until completely dissolved and smooth.
Cool.
Add yogurt and vanilla. Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Pour into can and freeze.
May add fruit to make
other flavors.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
In large mixer bowl, blend all ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: 1 2 3 4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix flour and baking powder; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350°. Check with toothpick for doneness.
Bake in 3 layer pans.
Serves 16.

title: patio beans
directions: Cook meat and drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Can be cooked in crock-pot.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; let sit overnight.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: good dessert
directions: Mix well pudding and pineapple juice.
Add crushed pineapple. Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and other ingredients.
Mix well and chill a few hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook first four ingredients until broccoli is tender.
Mix next 3 ingredients well.
Add rice.
Stir well.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry mix alternately with bananas, small amount at a time, beating until smooth.
Add nuts, if desired. Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour and 10 minutes, until done.
(Makes 1 loaf.)

title: cherry pudding deluxe
directions: Line a well buttered pan with 2 cups of cherries.
Cream together 3/4 cup white sugar and 3 tablespoons butter, then add 1 cup sifted flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt, alternating with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour this batter over the cherries.

title: marinated chicken grill and grilled chicken salad
directions: Place chicken in Ziploc bag.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate 24 to 48 hours.
Grill.
Serve grilled chicken with rice and vegetables as an entree for 4 to 6 people. Use remaining chicken for salad for 4 to 6 people the next day, preparing as follows.

title: microwave vanilla cream pie
directions: In a 2-quart mixing bowl, blend sugar, cornstarch or flour and salt.
Add milk, stirring until well mixed.
Microwave at High for 8 to 12 minutes or until thick, stirring with wire whip 3 or 4 times.
Stir some hot mixture into egg yolks.
Blend egg yolk mixture into remaining hot mixture.
Microwave at High for 1 minute.
Blend in butter and vanilla, stirring until butter melts. Pour into baked pie crusts.
Place plastic wrap or waxed paper on top until cool to prevent skin from forming.

title: shrimp combo
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Serve over cooked rice.
Season with Tabasco sauce.
Serves 4.

title: delicious and easy bread
directions: Beat eggs and add it with the milk to all of the dry ingredients. Put in two greased loaf pans. Let stand for 1/2 hour. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: crusty chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in a shallow 2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Place 1 slice Swiss cheese on each piece of chicken.
Stir together chicken soup and wine.
Spoon evenly over chicken.
At this point, you may refrigerate until ready to cook, up to overnight.
When ready to bake, sprinkle crushed croutons over top.
Evenly drizzle butter over croutons.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt over hot water 1/2 cup peanut butter morsels.
Stir until smooth; set aside.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in melted morsels.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Alternately blend in flour and milk.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake until crust is golden, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Form into a log and refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve on crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and press into pan.
Cover with ketchup and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and cook to soft ball stage; remove from heat.
In a mixing bowl combine butter, Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter plus vanilla.
Add to cooked syrup and beat.
When mixed, pour into buttered pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: lemon sauce
directions: In small saucepan, mix cornstarch, sugar and salt. Add water, food color and lemon juice. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Spoon over chicken.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together for 20 minutes.
Watch that it doesn't stick and add 1/4 cup water as necessary.
Add the cheese, half and half and cream of celery soup, in that order. Heat and stir together until blended.
Do not boil.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, heat the milk chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted and smooth.
Remove saucepan from heat; stir in marshmallows and walnuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a waxed paper lined baking sheet.
Chill in the refrigerator for 15 minutes or until firm.
Put in a bowl with a sealed lid. Can be refrigerated up to 1 week.

title: kahlua fruit dip
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve with fruit chunks. Yield: 20 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450° to 475°.
Mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal. Stir in buttermilk with a fork until soft dough forms.
Knead until workable and roll to desired thickness.
Bake approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican beans
directions: Cook pinto beans until half done. Add all other ingredients and cook additional 2 1/2 hours.

title: cobbler crust
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add salt and flour; mix well. Spoon over fruit.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and mix. Add apples and nuts. Mix well. Combine all other ingredients and add to dry mixture. Mix well. Grease and flour 9 x 12 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk.
Allow to stand until milk is absorbed.
Stir and thoroughly combine with bran-milk mixture, melted shortening, egg, apple, sugar and cinnamon.
Add flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.
Stir only until all ingredients are just blended.
Pour into 12 muffin pans. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: jane's 10 can soup
directions: Mix all of the chosen ingredients and add any others which might fit your taste in a large pot.
Salt will probably not be necessary, but add pepper and salt to taste.
Heat to boiling. Let this simmer for as long as it takes to bake the corn bread or French rolls.
Serve hot!
This keeps very well in the refrigerator for several days.
Enjoy!

title: cranberry meat balls
directions: Mix
first
7 ingredients together and form into balls. If desired,
brown in skillet on top of stove.
Mix cranberry sauce, chilli
sauce
and	brown
sugar together.	Place meat balls
in ovensafe
dish and pour mixture over them.	Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese and chili dip
directions: In Pyrex baking dish, spread the cream cheese for bottom layer.
Empty can of chili as next layer.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to broil and continue to bake for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chocolate chip zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
While still beating, gradually add sugar, oil and vanilla. Stir in melted chocolate and zucchini.

title: corn bread
directions: Bake in a square 8-inch cake pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Mix in peanut butter and vanilla; stir well.
Place corn flakes in bottom of pan.
Pour all ingredients over flakes and cut into squares.
You may need to add to or take away from ingredients according to your taste.

title: basic french toast
directions: Combine 1st 3 ingredients.
Dip bread in this mixture and brown each side on a well-buttered griddle or skillet.
Serve hot. May sprinkle with sugar.

title: "chicken wiggle"
directions: Cook and chop chicken (reserve 1/2 cup broth).	Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook vegetables (peas and chopped celery, carrot).
Cook soups with milk and the 1/2 cup broth.
Mix together and add pimientos (if desired).
Stir gently over low heat or bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: m&m pretzel candy
directions: Using cookie sheet with sides, place pretzels on cookie sheet with salty side up. Top with chocolate disks. Bake for 5 minutes in 225-degree oven. Remove and put an M&M in the center, pressing slightly.
Cool until set.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Knead in peanut butter. Roll into balls (quarter size).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping blend well; fold in strawberries. Spoon into crust; freeze until firm approximately 4 hours or over night. Garnish with additional whole strawberries if desired. Let stand at room temp. For 10 minutes before serving. Store leftovers in freezer.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
In a heavy skillet, brown chops in oil for 5 minutes on each side.
Drain excess oil.
Pour Ragu sauce over chops while cooking.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mom's beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in about 6 cups water, then add tomato sauce, onion, garlic cloves, brown sugar, molasses, mustard and liquid smoke.
Add a ham hock or 4 slices of bacon (diced) or a small piece of salt pork.
Bring all just to a boil, then simmer for 3 to 4 hours or until beans cook.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pecan turtles
directions: In a double boiler, melt caramels, adding milk.
When melted, add pecans.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Melt chocolate with paraffin.
Dip caramels into chocolate.
Cool on wax paper.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Measure 3 cups sweet milk; sift or mix together sugar, cocoa and 1 cup of the milk.
Put the other 2 cups on the stove, medium heat.
When hot, you have your eggs and flour and sugar and cocoa all ready beaten together to get out all the lumps, so when you add it to the hot milk, you stir continuously with a metal pancake turner.
With this you keep the bottom of pot from burning.
(Or can pour egg mixture through a strainer that will keep out the lumps as well.)

title: chicken bodine
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together tuna and cream of chicken soup.
Add chopped onion, pepper and mayonnaise.
Mix and add the stuffing.
Add milk to mix together.
Pack firmly into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes and uncovered until brown.

title: life's recipe("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Cream greetings and smiles thoroughly.
Add handshakes beaten slightly.
Add love slowly.
Sift in sympathy and hospitality and serve with humility.

title: beef rolls with dressing
directions: Pound meat into thin pieces about 4 x 5 inches.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix everything but marshmallows in slow cooker.
Cover.
Cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.
Place in baking dish and cover with marshmallows.
Brown 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: fruit mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add balance.
Double recipe fills 2 1/2-quart ring mold.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Grease
quart
baking
dish.
Stir together all ingredients.
Pour
into
prepared dish.
Place dish in baking pan (filled
with hot water to depth of 1 inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serves 6.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown meat and onion; blend in pizza sauce, garlic salt and oregano.
Put mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with Mozzarella.

title: tomato salsa(canned)
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick (will cook down until about 1/2 of original amount).
Seal in jars in warm water bath.

title: pig eating cake
directions: Mix and bake in 3 (8-inch) pans at 350°.

title: spicy chicken and rice
directions: In a large saucepan, heat chicken broth, tomatoes, garlic and dried basil to boiling.
Add rice. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add undrained chicken, peas and hot pepper sauce. Cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Garnish with basil leaves and red pepper rings.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, tapioca, salt and nutmeg.
Add rhubarb and strawberries, mix well to coat fruit.
Let stand 20 minutes. Spoon fruit into pastry lined 9 inch pie plate.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Moisten pastry edge.
Top with lattice crust; flute edge.
Bake in hot oven (400 degrees) for 35-40 minutes.
If desired, decorate lattice top with additional sliced fresh strawberries dipped in melted currant jelly.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg
whites until stiff, put in the sugar and beat again. Then
fold
in
the
other ingredients and pour into a greased pie plate.
Bake
for
30 minutes at 350°.
It is good served with Cool Whip or plain.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Add apples.
Sift together flour, soda and salt three times.
Pour into two 9-inch greased pans lined with waxed paper.
Put in cold oven.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas
and
add
filling.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1/2 cup boiling	water.	Add
half
and half and pour over dish.
Add cheese.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip, Jell-O, mandarin oranges and nuts. Mix well. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place butter on large double thickness of foil, spreading to grease foil.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, cheese and cream.
Bring foil together over potatoes and fold into secure package.
Grill over flame at medium to high setting at least 20 to 25 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: irish jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Cool and thicken. Beat with electric beater. Add mayonnaise and cottage cheese.
Continue beating.
Stir in crushed pineapple plus juice and nuts.
Pour into large Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: never fail hot rolls
directions: Melt Crisco; set aside.
Dissolve yeast with 1/4 cup hot water.
Add Crisco, egg, other water, sugar, salt and flour.
Mix and store in fridge at least 2 hours.
Roll out.
Let rise.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix the flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping and spread on cooled crust.
Beat pudding and milk until thick; then spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: aunt lorena's date loaf candy
directions: In a large saucepan, boil sugar, milk, butter and salt until a little mixture forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water, about 250° on a candy thermometer.
Stir occasionally to keep from scorching.
Stir in dates; cook until tender.
Take from fire and beat until cool and thick.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour half onto wet cloth and roll into a log shape.
Repeat for the other half.
Store in the refrigerator; cut in slices to serve.
This is a very old family recipe.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Peel and slice zucchini.
Coat zucchini with flour or cornmeal, salt and pepper to taste.
Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown.

title: butterscotch apple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients; add to egg mixture and mix well (batter will be stiff). Stir in apples and nuts. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Butterscotch chips are sprinkled over top of batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookie bars
directions: Pour melted margarine over sugars in mixing bowl.
Mix well. Add eggs and beat.
Beat in flour which has been sifted with soda and salt.
Add vanilla.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts. Put dough into 9 x 12-inch loaf pan and bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake!
Cool and slice.

title: jo-jo's
directions: Mix together the egg and milk.
Mix together the flour, seasoning, salt and pepper.

title: oat baked chicken
directions: Serve open-faced on Pepperidge Farm dinner rolls with a slice of olive on top, or serve on bread of your choice.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend cheese with mayonnaise.
Add nuts, green peppers and drained fruit; mix well.
Fold in whipped cream with dash of salt. Pour into individual freezing molds and freeze until firm.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with cherries.

title: delicious baked chicken
directions: Clean and wash chicken.
Mix all of the ingredients and season the chicken with the mixed ingredients well.
Place the chicken in a
well-greased
baking
pan;
bake
in the covered baking pan for 2 hours
Remove the cover and bake an additional 1/2 hour,
so
the
chicken
will
become
a golden brown.
It might become
a
golden brown in less time than the suggested half hour. If
so,
remove from oven and serve when convenient.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add garlic, salt, basil, tomato sauce and tomato paste; cook for 15 minutes.
In bowl, add parsley, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Mix together.
Cook lasagna noodles.
In large casserole dish, lay noodles and sauce mix and mixture in bowl.
Also add Mozzarella cheese.
Alternate noodles and all ingredients until gone.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix well with herb stuffing mix.
Mix with Stove Top mix.
Place this mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 320° for 1 hour.

title: ida craver's pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine or butter and Crisco together.
Add the sugar gradually, beating after each addition.
Beat the eggs until light and fluffy and add to the butter-sugar mixture, blending thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add the flavorings to the milk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with the flour.
When well blended, pour into a well-greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: chocolate ice cream pie
directions: Blend together lightly the ice cream and milk.
Add pudding. Beat until just mixed, about 1 minute.
Pour into baked pie shell. Let stand in refrigerator about 1 hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries into pie shell.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O and water until thick.
Pour over strawberries.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: macaroni and meat casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Cook meat and onion until lightly browned.
Drain off fat.
Combine with meat, soup, eggs, milk and shredded cheese.
Add macaroni.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Cream margarine and 1/3 cup sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Spread dough onto bottom and 1 1/2 inches high around sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: pumpkin chews
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Combine sugars, shortening, cinnamon and nutmeg; blend well.
Beat in egg; gradually mix in dry ingredients, mixing alternately with pumpkin.
Stir in chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: green enchiladas(student favorite)
directions: Cut tortillas into fourths.
Use 1/2 of them to line an oblong baking dish, sprayed with cooking spray.
Top tortillas with ground meat, then onion, then grated Cheddar cheese.
Add the other 1/2 of the tortillas.
Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Next, add milk, chilies (drained) and the Velveeta cheese which has been diced or grated.
Do not boil, but cook until thick.
Pour over tortilla-meat combination and heat in oven for about 20 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms. Pull
stems out and put small amount of sausage inside.
Put
stems
back
in
mushrooms.
Mix egg and milk. Dip mushrooms in egg mixture, then dip in flour. Do this again, so batter
is thick.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Use Ranch dressing for dip.

title: rice and pigeon peas(arroz con gandules)
directions: Saute ham and salt pork.
Add peppers, tomatoes, onion, tomato sauce and garlic; simmer for a few minutes.
Add capers, olives, achiote coloring and rice.
Mix well and let cook for two to three minutes.
Add the pigeon peas, water and salt.
Mix thoroughly. Cook slowly until the liquid has evaporated.
Stir, cover and cook until the rice is tender.
Serve hot.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and press into oblong pan. Do not grease the pan.
Mix the remaining and pour over the cake mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
I put it in fridge and liked it better cold.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Whip all ingredients together; put in pie crust.
Cool 4 hours.
Serve with favorite fruit as topping.

title: chicken speonk
directions: Cook spinach per label, drain, spread in warm iron pan. Saute scallions in butter for 1-2 minutes.
Add chicken breasts, salt and pepper and simmer, covered, in wine and chicken broth for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove and layer on spinach, save liquid (about 1+ cup). Warm slices of Canadian bacon in the liquid and place on chicken. Add mushrooms, garlic to wine/broth mix, simmer 3 minutes.
Add soup and bring to boil.
Spread over chicken. Sprinkle with grated cheese and breadcrumbs.
Bake to melt or better yet, broil until bubbling.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, celery, green peppers and onion tops.
Add ham and sausage.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add rest except shrimp.
Cover pan and cook.
Season shrimp with Creole seasoning, black pepper and garlic powder.
Add shrimp and cook 5 minutes more.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: texas chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Mix margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Stir and bring to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar. Stir well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onion, pepper and parsley.
Add cooked rice to sausage mix.
Add melted cheese (in milk) to rice.
Mix in 2-quart container.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, add seasonings (optional).
Pour in a large dish, top with cheese (optional) and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: streusel pudding coffee cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, except Streusel Topping.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Spread in pan. Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 400° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar and pudding mix, stirring with a wire whisk to remove lumps.
Add oil, eggs, water and sour cream, stirring until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green peppers.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain mixture and mix with tomatoes.
Arrange zucchini in a 9 1/2-inch square casserole dish.
Alternate layers of zucchini and hamburger mixture, ending with zucchini.
Top with cheese.
Microwave for 30 to 45 minutes on High.

title: fran's baked beans(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Drain off a little of liquid from the beans. Mix all ingredients together; put in a large dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving portions.
Brown well in large skillet.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Spoon the sauce over the ribs 2 or 3 times during the cooking period.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes until sauce coats ribs.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put into casserole dish. Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding and crushed pineapple well.
Add pecans and Cool Whip; mix well.
Put in refrigerator.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Pressure hen.
Discard skin and bones.
Save broth.
Pressure squirrels, bone and save two cups of broth. Mix all ingredients, except corn, into a large heavy pot.
(We use old pressure canners.)
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Add corn.
Stir from bottom of pot constantly for 30 to 45 minutes or until thick.
May add water if becomes too thick. Freezes well.

title: mom's pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks slightly; add one half of sugar, the pumpkin, milk, salt and spices.
Put in double boiler and cook and stir until mixture thickens. Stir in soaked gelatin until it is dissolved.
Cool. Whip the egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon salt until stiff, beating in the remainder of the sugar.
When pumpkin begins to set, fold in egg white mixture.
Fill pie shell.
Chill for several hours. Garnish with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: mexican chocolate drink
directions: In a 4-cup measuring cup, put chocolate, coffee and 1/2 cup water.
Heat for 5 minutes in a microwave oven.
Remove from oven and stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat for 8 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grandma's bryant chicken and dressing
directions: Mix together cornmeal, flour, oil, milk, eggs and butter. Mix well. If too thick, add some water. Pour into a large greased iron skillet. Bake at 450° for about 30 minutes or until browned. Cool. Mix together chopped chicken, onion, sage, salt, pepper and soup. Add 4 cups of saved chicken broth. Add crumbing cornbread. Pour into a large glass lasagna pan. Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: onion rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in butter, place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in covered casserole (buttered) at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown beef. Add onions and celery. Simmer until tender. Combine with the rest.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have cream cheese and butter at room temperature.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat 1 minute after each addition.
Add dry ingredients 1/3 at a time alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat well after each addition. Pour into a well-greased and floured tube (Bundt) pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Then turn onto wire rack and cool thoroughly before slicing.
Sprinkle lightly with confectioners sugar.

title: date log cookies
directions: Mix vanilla wafer crumbs and milk.
Add dates and nuts.
Put on wax paper.
Wet your hands while putting the mixture together. Roll mixture in a roll; take the roll and cover it with confectioners sugar.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Chill 10 to 12 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together broccoli, raisins, onions and bacon.
Make dressing by mixing mayonnaise, Sweet 'N Low and vinegar together. Pour over broccoli mixture and chill before serving.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, salt and vanilla. Fold in nuts. Drop by tsp. onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325 degrees for about 30 minutes. Sift powdered sugar over tarts while still hot.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Add pineapple (including liquid). Add marshmallows and nuts.
Blend well!

title: teriyaki steak barbecue marinade(and beef kabobs)
directions: Mix all ingredients well until sugar is dissolved.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Marinate meat for 1 to 2 hours.
More time gives more flavor.

title: butterscotch and chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat a 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray. Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in large bowl until well blended. Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Fold in the walnuts. Pour mixture into prepared pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and butterscotch flavored chips over mixture in pan. Bake until a toothpick inserted in center of brownies comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Cut into 16 squares to serve.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Make a couple hours before serving so that the flavors and cream have a chance to blend.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Mix evaporated milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 12 minutes or until thick.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Frost cooled cake immediately.
Makes 2 1/2 cups frosting.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Form meat into patties.
Place patties in the refrigerator for about 30 minutes before cooking.
Grill outside on outdoor grill or on a Jen-Aire grill inside for best results.
Baste patties with barbecue sauce while cooking.
Cook about 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Place a slice of fat-free cheese on each patty for the last minute of cooking time.
Serve on low-fat buns with lettuce, tomato and any other garnish you desire.
If using mayonnaise, be sure and use the Kraft fat-free variety.
Yields 8 turkey burgers (6 ounce patties).

title: overnight-layered green salad
directions: Shred lettuce and place in shallow serving dish (9 x 13-inch). Top with green onions, celery and water chestnuts.
Open frozen peas, break peas apart and sprinkle over layers.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over top and sprinkle with sugar, Parmesan cheese, seasoning salt and garlic powder (mix these 4 ingredients together).
Cover and chill overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle with 3 hard-cooked eggs and chopped and crumbled bacon.
Cut tomatoes in wedges and place over the top.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° to 400° for about 35 to 45 minutes.
Should be golden brown and done inside.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour batter in two pans (8-inch round).
Bake as directed on cake mix box.
Cool 10 minutes. Prick with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

title: sausage and cheese squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Unroll crescent roll dough. Place dough in bottom of ungreased rectangular baking dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 inches. Press seams closed and push dough 1 inch up sides of baking dish. Arrange sausage evenly on dough. Sprinkle with bell pepper and 1 cup of the cheese. Beat soup and eggs until blended; pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: curried lentil soup with tomato and spinach
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cook and stir onions in oil over moderate heat. When golden, add garlic and ginger.
Cook and stir mixture for 1 minute.
Add curry powder and cumin and cook 30 seconds. Add the lentils and 1 1/4 cup water.
Bring mixture to boil and then simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth and simmer, covered, for 25 minutes.
Stir in the tomatoes and spinach and simmer for 2 minutes.
Season the soup with lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 3 cups.
Serves 2.
Can add leftover ham for a more substantial soup.

title: jamboree peach cobber
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Sift together flour, 1 cup of sugar, salt and baking powder and blend with milk. Pour mixture over melted butter. Spread peaches over this and sprinkle with other cup of sugar mixed with cinnamon. Bake 1 hour. Crust will magically appear and cover entire surface of cobbler. Makes 1 cobbler.

title: pickled okra
directions: Put spices in bottom of jar.
Heat vinegar, water and salt together.
Pack okra in jars and pour vinegar over okra.
Seal jars.

title: grilled t-bones with herb butter
directions: In a small bowl, soften butter and mix with chopped herbs. Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Grill steaks over medium-hot heat on grill for 10 minutes on each side for medium-rare doneness. Serve steaks with herb butter.

title: bourbon balls
directions: In a heavy saucepan, heat chocolate pieces over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and corn syrup.
Stir in bourbon until well mixed.
Add vanilla wafers and nuts to chocolate mixture and mix well.
Let stand about 30 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a jelly roll pan.
Blend all ingredients together about 20 seconds; then beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Pour into a pan.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Stir in chow mein noodles.
Drop onto wax paper and let cool.

title: hawaiian soda
directions: Place 2 tablespoons pineapple, 2 teaspoons cherries and 1 tablespoon banana in each of 6 tall glasses.
Make 6 balls of ice cream.
Place 1 ball in each glass.
Stir to blend with fruit. Fill glass almost to the top with the orange soda.
Make 6 more balls of ice cream from remaining pint.
Top each soda with ice cream ball and serve immediately.
Garnish with whipped cream and a whole cherry, if desired.

title: eggplant mozzarella
directions: Slice eggplant 1/4 inch thick; dip in beaten eggs, then in bread crumbs (2 times).
Fry in oil until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
In a large baking pan (sprayed with Pam) layer the eggplant, then spaghetti sauce and the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix and spoon in pan.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Mix the ingredients in saucepan and add 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Cook over heat until clear and thick.
Cover with wax paper until cool.

title: papoose pie
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip. When mixed well, layer in 2 graham cracker pie crusts, starting with bananas and ending layering with mix.
Cover with blueberries.
Chill and serve.

title: trifle
directions: Line a large, shallow dish with cut sponge cake.
Spread with jam or jelly.
Cover with cubed fruit.
Soak the fruit and cake with a small cup of sherry.
Make up the vanilla pudding or custard according to the directions.
When cool, pour over the sponge cake-fruit mixture.
Allow to cool completely.
Pipe the cream in whatever shape you wish or spread in a thin layer over the custard. Finish with halved cherries, angelica or Hundreds and Thousands. Serve cold.

title: super hot dog casserole
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, relish, mayonnaise, onion and mustard in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Cut each frankfurter in half lengthwise.
Insert frankfurter pieces upright around edge of mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put chuck roast in shallow pan.
Spread top of roast with A.1. sauce, then pour Lipton soup mix over top of A.1.
Pour cream of mushroom soup all over top (very little water in pan).
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook the meat.
Add the taco seasoning mix.
Heat refried beans and chili peppers together.
Add layers as follows:
burrito shells, 1/2 refried beans, 1/2 hamburger meat, 1/2 corn, 1/2 of both cheeses and 1/2 of olives and peppers. Repeat.
Cover with foil; heat until the cheese melts.

title: marble squares
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, sugar and egg in saucepan.
Bring margarine, water and chocolate to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Use wooden spoon to stir in flour and sugar mixture; add sour cream, soda, salt and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Spoon cream cheese over batter; cut through with spatula.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: duck and sauerkraut
directions: Wipe duck, inside and out.
Sprinkle cavity with salt and pepper.
Dust outside with flour, salt and pepper.
In deep kettle, slowly brown duck on all sides in shortening.
Remove from heat.
Stuff cavity loosely with sauerkraut.
Put duck back in kettle, cover with any remaining sauerkraut and its juice.
Add water, simmer 1 hour or until duck is tender.
Check ever so often to be sure there is liquid in bottom of kettle; add water if necessary.
Serve on long platter surrounded by kraut.
Mashed potatoes are a must with this.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring potatoes, bouillon cubes and onion to a boil. Add milk, garlic salt, salt, pepper, margarine and parsley flakes. Reduce heat and let simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: butterscotch sauce(ice cream topping)
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler; mix well.
Cook until thick.
Stir frequently.
Stir before serving.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bones.
Save 2 or 3 cups of broth. In a large kettle, add chicken, broth and all vegetables.
Simmer. Add ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.

title: fruitcake *
directions: Chop nuts and fruit, mix lightly with flour.
Stir in milk and pack into well-greased or wax paper lined pan about the size of a broiler pan.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: carl's chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Saute chicken with garlic for about 5 minutes, turning chicken often.
Remove garlic.
Add salt, pepper, rosemary, anchovies, vinegar and wine.
Simmer uncovered until liquid is reduced by one-third.
Dissolve tomato paste in bouillon.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer covered for 20 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat milk until bubbles form around edge of pan. Add 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1/2 cup butter. Add unseasoned mashed potatoes. Cool to lukewarm.

title: carameled yams
directions: Cook yams, cool and peel.
Layer yams in a baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and flour together and place on top of the yams.
Next, add oleo, cream, marshmallows and nuts on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into crust; bake for 30 minutes.
Chill.
Spread with whipped cream. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lemonade lime-jello pie
directions: Add boiling water and sugar to Jell-O.
Let dissolve.
Add lemonade and chill until just set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie shell and place in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Cook macaroni by directions.
Saute onions in butter. Add meat and cook until brown. Combine macaroni and all ingredients, except cheese, in a large greased casserole bowl.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Drain peaches; reserving juice.
Arrange peaches on a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread can of pudding on top of peaches.
Mix cake mix, using peach juice instead of water.
Spread batter over peaches and pudding.
Bake according to cake mix directions.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: In large deep skillet, brown steak strips in vegetable oil over medium heat 3 minutes.
Add onion and garlic; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Add soy sauce, tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and sugar. Heat to boiling, stirring often to dissolve sugar.
Add green pepper strips and celery and heat through.
Mix cornstarch with sherry until smooth.
Add to skillet; bring back to a low boil, stirring until sauce is thickened and translucent.
Stir in mushrooms.
Serve over rice.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and add seasoned salt and pepper and chopped onion.
Drain off fat and set aside.
Heat enchilada sauce in saucepan and set aside.
Heat about 2 inches of oil in another saucepan and dip tortilla into oil, enough to soften.
Drain on paper towel and place on a plate.
Fill tortilla with ground beef, onion and cheese; roll up and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Continue to fill, roll up and place filled tortillas into pan until full.
Then pour remaining sauce over all and sprinkle cheese.
Top with diced olives and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli, cheese and 1 can soup.
Layer the rest in the same order, except soup.
Add eggs, then the last of the soup. Cover with the Ritz crackers and butter.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pet milk company gourmet macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix macaroni, mushrooms and pimiento in a greased casserole. Stir cheese, milk, onion, mustard, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir into macaroni.
Top with cheese and tomato slices.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix it all together with hands.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 10-15 minutes or until brown.

title: oriental chicken and mushrooms
directions: Place chicken in a 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion flakes.
In small bowl, combine soy sauce, honey and garlic powder.
Pour evenly over chicken.
Cover and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread green pepper and mushrooms evenly over chicken.
Continue to bake (covered) 20 more minutes.

title: low-fat green pepper dip
directions: In a blender, puree the green pepper and onion.
Add the cottage cheese (a little at a time).
Add the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flavorings and beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: grampie furrough's baked beans
directions: Pick over beans and soak overnight in cold water.
Parboil beans until outside of skins can be broken between thumb and forefinger.
Place salt pork and onion in bottom of crock-pot. Add beans and other ingredients.
Cover with water. Cook in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low or 4 to 5 hours on high.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Put this mixture on both sides of steak.
Preheat electric frypan to 350°.
Put oil in skillet and brown steak on both sides.
Lower heat to 260° and cook 10 more minutes, turning occasionally.
Place steak on platter.
Add milk to skillet slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over steak and serve.

title: chicken tostadas
directions: Toss chicken with salsa.
Spread tostada shells with cream cheese product.
Top with chicken mixture, lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Serve with additional salsa and jalapeno pepper slices, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.
Preparation Time: 20 minutes.

title: oreo cream cheese pie
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and pat in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes on top of oven rack.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Mix ingredients together, except butter.
Dip chicken into melted butter and then into mixture.
Coat well.
Place in baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: barbecue sauce - dietetic
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked onion.
Add touch of garlic powder, sweetener and hot sauce (if desired.).
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: the best chicken enchiladas ever!(international mexican)
directions: Boil chicken and break into pieces, discarding skin.
Add all ingredients into a two-quart saucepan and cook until cheeses are melted.
Take tortillas and spread 1/3 cup mixture in tortilla and roll tortilla up.
Place filled tortillas in 9 x 13-inch sprayed pan.
Sprinkle more cheese, olives and onions on top for garnish. Cover pan with foil and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with Spanish rice and refried beans.

title: sparkling sangria punch
directions: In a large pitcher or punch bowl, combine water, orange juice, pink grapefruit juice, lime juice and half of the orange and lime slices.
Chill, covered, until cold or up to 24 hours.
Just before serving, pour in 2 bottles of sparkling grape juice or ginger ale.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with remaining orange and lime slices.
Makes 24 (4 oz.) servings.

title: cinnamon popcorn
directions: In a small bowl, use a spoon to stir together the melted margarine and cinnamon.
Put the popcorn in a large bowl.
Pour the margarine with cinnamon over the popcorn. Stir the popcorn to mix it with the margarine and cinnamon.

title: chocolate walnut drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together. Work butter with a spoon until creamy.
Add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and chocolate; blend well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Frost with buttercream frosting (usually on back of powdered sugar box).

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and let rise.
Place in refrigerator.
Use as desired.
Allow about two hours for rising. Shape into three small balls; place in muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Combine slightly beaten egg yolks, cooking oil and milk. Add to dry ingredients all at once; beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form when beater is raised; fold into batter.
Bake in preheated waffle iron at medium heat until steaming stops and waffle is golden brown, about 5 to 6 minutes.

title: hidden valley cheese puffs
directions: Mix the cheese, mayonnaise, and salad dressing mix together. Spread the mixture on the bread slices. Broil until puffed and golden brown. About 3 to 4 minutes.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add the sauces and optional ingredients to meat and simmer well.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer twice the noodles, meat sauce, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: mary's chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: cinnamon nut bars
directions: Mix in order, except nuts.
Press into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and press slightly on top of batter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix like whipped cream.

title: scramble
directions: Mix all together except bark.
Melt bark.
Pour over the other mixture; mix well. Spread in a shallow pan.
Let cool completely. Break in pieces.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cake layers
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil, milk and flour.
Add vanilla. Makes 3 layers.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sun pickles
directions: Put dill and garlic in the jar.
Mix water, vinegar and salt well; pour over pickles until full in jar.
Cover.
Set in sun for 2 days.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Combine flour, sugar, spices, salt and soda.
Make a well in the center of the mixture and add pumpkin, oil, eggs and water; mix well.
Pour into prepared pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: braised sirloin tips
directions: Brown meat in fat. Add beef consomme, red Burgundy wine, soy sauce, minced garlic and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Turn down heat and simmer until tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Combine cornstarch and hot water.
Pour into meat mixture and cook until thickened. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: potato and pork casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, water, parsley, soup, salt, pepper and seasonings.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Lay fried pork chops on top of mixture.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: In small bowl, combine ham, cheese, cream cheese, onions and red pepper.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap; chill.
Remove from refrigerator to soften before serving.
Makes 1 (2-cup) cheese ball.

title: broiled marshmallow frosting
directions: Cream the margarine. Add the brown sugar and blend well.

Stir in the cream. Add the nuts and marshmallows, mixing lightly. Spread on top of a baked 9-inch square chocolate cake (or white or yellow cake), which has not been removed from the pan. Broil slowly about 5-inches below heat for 2 or 3 minutes or until the top is bubbly and lightly browned.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Stir in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: chicken crescent puffs
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onions.
Separate crescent roll dough into 8 pieces.
Put chicken mixture on dough and pinch closed.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be used as an appetizer if made into 16 pieces, however only cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Beat together 2 cups confectioners sugar, 1/2 cup
butter
and
tablespoons
creme de menthe liquor. Spread on cool cake.

title: chili steak and beans
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and cumin; coat steak and brown in large skillet.
Stir in celery, onion, carrots, water and chili sauce (or salsa).
Heat to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until beef is tender, 45 to 60 minutes.
Add beans with liquid and green pepper.
Cover and simmer until beans are hot and green pepper is tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Pour salt over them and cover with water.
Add ice and hold down with a plate for 3 hours. Drain.

title: zippy tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer about 2 hours.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Microwave chicken breasts or use cooked chicken breasts.
While chicken is cooking, prepare stuffing mix as directed on the package.
Also, heat soup, adding 1/2 can of water or milk.
Cook carrots and peas for 5 minutes.
Cut up cooked chicken and mix with soup and peas and carrots.
Set aside. Using 1/2 stuffing mix, layer bottom of 8-inch baking pan, add chicken mixture on top and then cover with remaining stuffing. Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Diced potato or diced onion can be added to chicken mix if desired.

title: beef or pork stew
directions: Cut up onion, carrot, potato and celery.
Put broth in a pan and heat to boiling.
Add cut-up fresh vegetables and salt.
Cover and boil gently, about 20 minutes, until vegetables are tender.

title: quick chicken and noodles
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Stir.
Add noodles and chicken.
Heat through on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Mix well.
Mix 1 egg at a time, mixing well.
Alternate mixing flour and sour cream, ending with flour.
Add flavorings; mix well.
Grease and flour a Bundt tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let cake cool in pan for 20 to 30 minutes before removing.

title: shrimp marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate shrimp at least 8 hours in fridge.
Serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Blend until crumbly.
Pat into large pizza pan.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large bowl on High for 1 to 2 minutes until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese.
Put into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour. Sprinkle with remaining cheese the last 10 minutes.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Mix all ingredients; marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Bake on cookie sheet at 225° for 2 hours.
Baste and cook at 275° for 1 1/2 hours longer.

title: broccoli bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; stir.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more.
Add Velveeta or Cheez Whiz for variety.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread and bread.
Add onion soup mix, sage, pepper, salt and poultry seasoning.
Stir in eggs, celery soup, chicken soup and enough broth to make a very moist dressing. Place dressing in large roasting pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until browned.
Stir once or twice during the first 20 minutes of baking.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: pecans
directions: Cook five minutes. Pour in nuts. Stir and pour on waxed paper.

title: enchiladas verdes
directions: Heat oil in a small skillet.
Dip tortillas in oil for 10 seconds or until limber.
Drain on a paper towel.
Place 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 tablespoon onion on each tortilla and roll up.
Place tortilla seam side down in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: double chocolate rebels
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cocoa and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy. Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Alternately add water and dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Gradually add oats, stirring well.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Drop 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.
Don't overbake!

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown. Cream the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on cooled crust. Mix pudding and milk until thick. Spread on cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: peach crisp
directions: Toss peaches, 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish or a 9-inch deep dish pie plate. Set aside.
