title: chicken stir
directions: Cut chicken into strips and chunks.
Cook until all pink color is gone in butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce, barbecue sauce, bell pepper, onion and mixed vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Chicken amount may vary as to number to be fed.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar together well.
Add milk and oil; mix up well.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Put 1/2 dough in pie pan and pat to edges and up to rim.
Pat the other half on wax paper, dump on top of pie filling and crimp.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 crusts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix and blend together.
Put into buttered baking dish and bake at 350°
until brown.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add sour cream and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with Pineapple Icing.

title: low cholesterol brou muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Place brou
and
milk
in mixing bowl; stir.
Let stored until cereal is softened
(perhaps five minutes).
Add egg, oil and molasses. Beat
well;
add
sifted
dry ingredients, stirring only
until combined.
Put
butter
evenly
into
six greased muffin tins. Bake in preheated 400° oven for about 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill before serving.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: mixed bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Mix well. Bake in a preheated 250° oven for 3 hours.
Stir everything.

title: cheese puffs(diabetic recipe)
directions: Separate biscuits and cut into quarters.
Cut cheese into 40 small cubes.
Wrap a biscuit piece around a cheese cube and seal edges.
Melt margarine in pan.
Roll each biscuit in margarine and leave in pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes, until lightly browned. Makes 40 puffs.
Serving Size:
4 puffs equals 1 bread and 1 fat.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Fold in bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Add oil, vinegar, sugar and salt to cucumbers and onions in Tupperware.
Shake well and refrigerate overnight.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in oil about 5 minutes and drain.
Add soy sauce and water, simmer 10 minutes.
Add onions, celery and peppers, cut in length-wise strips.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper and cook until tender.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Follow the directions on the box of cake mix except reduce the water to 1/2 cup.
Add the canned pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice. Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake as directed.
Cool and frost with vanilla frosting mixed with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon. Decorate with candy pumpkins.

title: onion-n-dill potatoes
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, place potatoes and enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook over high heat until water comes to a full boil (4 to 6 minutes).
Reduce heat to medium.
Continue cooking until potatoes are fork-tender (8 to 12 minutes).
Drain potatoes, then return to pan (can quarter potatoes, if desired).
In a small bowl, stir together all remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Cook over medium heat, gently stirring, until thoroughly heated, 3 to 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spicy tortilla soup
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add chopped onion and process until smooth.
Measure 1/2 cup onion puree and set aside; reserve any remaining puree for other uses.

title: lamb chops
directions: Melt fat in large skillet; season chops with salt and pepper. Brown chops lightly on both sides.
Remove from skillet to baking pan.
Pour mushroom soup and water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until desired tenderness.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: In a heavy pan, cut and cube tenderloin and saute in butter, onions, peppers, garlic, salt and pepper until cooked.
Add cubed ham, nutmeg and cloves and simmer on low heat for 3 to 5 minutes. Add broth and cut up sausage; increase your heat.
Bring this mixture to a boil; add your rice and stir.
Lower your heat again and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and most of the liquid has been absorbed.
Pour into serving dish and sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Serve hot!

title: salsa
directions: Peel, chop and seed tomatoes.
Allow to drain in a colander. Chop onions and peppers (put through food processor).
In large pot over high heat combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes to 1 hour or until thick.
Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased baking dish at 350° for approximately 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: pie peaches
directions: Cook ingredients until thick, about 1 hour.
After it comes to a boil, put in pint jars and seal.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix thoroughly; chill and serve with veggies.

title: "hermits" ii
directions: Boil raisins 20 minutes in small amount of water; drain. Cream margarine and sugar, add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: fan sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes or just scrub and rinse. Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a wooden spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour before measuring, then add spices and salt to the flour. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Add the raisins, dates and nuts by hand, mixing well.
Add jam last. Bake in lightly greased Teflon tube pan (angel food cake pan) at 325° about 2 hours. Treat like fruitcake. Store 1 month before eating.
May be kept in cool place up to 1 year.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion and hamburger in butter.
Add seasonings.
Spread 3 cups cabbage in 2-quart baking dish; cover with meat mixture. Top with remaining cabbage; pour soup over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican appetizers
directions: In a mixer, mix all ingredients together except tortillas. Spread medium-thick layer on tortilla and roll up like a jelly roll.
Put in freezer for about 15 minutes. Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.
Serve with salsa. Great for office potlucks!

title: lemon curd
directions: In the top of a double boiler, beat eggs and sugar. Stir in butter, lemon juice, peel and salt. Cook over simmering water for 15 minutes or until mixture is thickened and reaches 160°. Cover and store in the refrigerator for up to 1 week. Serve chilled with scones, biscuits or English muffins. Yield: 3 1/2 cups.

title: elby's strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Cook over slow heat until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello.
Chill until thick.
Layer in a baked 9-inch pie shell with berries.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each egg.
Add sour cream and flour alternately.
Beat well; add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, if desired, or lemon.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in well-greased and floured tube pan.

title: coconut tembleque(serves 8)
directions: In a saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in part of the coconut milk.
Add remaining coconut milk and rest of ingredients.
Cook over moderate-high heat, stirring constantly.
As soon as it begins to thicken, reduce heat to moderate and stir until it boils and thickens.
Pour immediately into a pan, rinsed with cold water.
When thoroughly cool, turn onto a serving platter or cut in pieces.

title: creamy citrus chicken
directions: Saute chicken in oil and margarine until golden.
Add broth, garlic and thyme.
Bring to boil; lower heat, cover and simmer until chicken is cooked through.
Remove chicken to platter.
Stir together the sour cream and cornstarch.
Stir in orange juice until blended.
Stir into juices in pan.
Simmer for 2 minutes, stirring until thickened.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Put peppers, tomatoes and onion through the medium knife of a food chopper.
Sprinkle with salt and allow to stand 4 hours. Drain.
Combine vinegar and sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Add the vegetables and spices.
Bring again to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pack and seal at once.

title: homemade ice cream(low calorie)
directions: Pour into container without stirring.
Churn approximately 30 minutes.
Remove paddles and pack for 15 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat egg and milk together. Sift dry ingredients together, then add egg and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into hot grease, making pinwheel (funnel motion). Coat with powdered sugar.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Dredge in flour, salt and pepper. Brown in fat.
Add mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Stir in broth. Cover for 1 hour.
Add sour cream and heat.
Do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix soups, wine and wild rice; marinate for a few hours in large casserole.
Add chicken breasts; cook for 1 hour at 325° to 350°.
Remove cover and stir.
Replace cover and cook in oven for 1 more hour.

title: chicken & stuffing casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and cook with celery and onions until tender. In a bowl, mix mushroom soup, mushrooms, sour cream and pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish.
In another bowl mix together melted butter, 1 cup chicken broth and stuffing mix. Pour over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron while preparing batter.
Melt butter; set aside to cool.
Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Gradually add butter and buttermilk.
Beat until well blended.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix until batter is smooth.
Beat egg whites until round peaks form. Gently fold into batter.
Pour batter into center of hot waffle iron and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add horseradish, chili sauce, and other ingredients except shrimp.
Beat well until smooth and add shrimp. Chill.

title: marinade for flank steak
directions: Mix together; pour over steak.
Marinate overnight.
Discard marinade before broiling steak.

title: original barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer your meat (ribs, pork or chicken) in the sauce until tender.
Put on grill or in oven to brown.
Continue basting with the sauce.

title: west virginia stew
directions: In a large soup pan, cut up potatoes in small chunks and shred the cabbage.
Add stew meat and salt.
Fill pan with water 4 inches from the top.
Cover; cook until cabbage is tender.
Drain water until it is half full in pan.
Add all remaining ingredients; cook for 30 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and add sugar.
Then mix in all flour.
Knead dough, adding a little flour, if sticky.
Roll into long, thin strips and twist into shape.
Brush with beaten egg over all pretzels and sprinkle with salt.

title: picnic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, blend Catalina dressing with honey.
Dip chicken into dressing mixture and then roll in crumbs, coating well.
Place in foil-lined large shallow baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes or until tender.
Good hot or cold. Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish and refrigerate.

title: broccoli cheese delight
directions: Combine water, butter and minced onion; bring to boil.
Add the frozen chopped broccoli; bring to boil again.
Add the Minute rice.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Add cream of celery soup and Cheez Whiz.
Stir mixture until well mixed. Pour into dish; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber-onion dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well. Chill and serve with vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg slightly. Add water and vinegar.
Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll out on Tupperware's pastry sheet which has been lightly floured.

title: summertime potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Bring water to a boil; add potatoes.
Return to a boil; cook about 6 minutes or until tender, being careful not to overcook.
Drain thoroughly; transfer to a large bowl.
Chill.

title: villa montana salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and whirl until well blended.
This is a most delicious dressing for tossed green salads.
I am never without it.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak navy beans overnight. Cook slowly for 2 hours. Peel and dice potatoes. Cook until done. Mash potatoes thoroughly. Add to beans. Chop onion and garlic. Add to beans and potatoes along with the bacon drippings. Add 4 cups water. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook mixture slowly until onions are tender. Serve hot.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using low speed of mixer until blended.
Pour into small bowl and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: 3 minute fudge(from betty crocker's cookbook)
directions: Butter square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Combine milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 225° on candy thermometer or until mixture spins a thread about 2-inches long when dropped from a spoon.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows, chocolate pieces, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until marshmallows and chocolate pieces are melted.
Pour mixture into pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds or 64 (1-inch) squares.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients, then fold in egg whites.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place the chicken in long greased baking dish sprinkled with salt and pepper.

Top with sauerkraut evenly over top, then Swiss cheese slices all over and pour the dressing evenly all over. Cover with foil and bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted into chicken with ease.
If you like can sprinkle 3/4 cup buttered rye bread crumbs on top before baking.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Rinse and place in rectangular pan. Pan fry bacon, onions and drippings over cooked spaghetti.
Add sugar to tomato puree (sweetened to taste) and pour puree and tomatoes over spaghetti; stir.
Cook mixture in 375° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until sauce is firm.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done. Cook rice until done. In a large dish, put rice, onion, both cans of soup, bell pepper and the chicken broth. Place chicken on top of rice and cook in oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 450°.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar in a bowl until light.
Add cooled melted butter, milk and vanilla extract.
Add flour and baking powder and beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gently fold into batter.
Bake and serve.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Mix brown sugar and 1 1/4 cups water and heat to boiling point.
Combine cornstarch and salt with remaining 1/4 cup water. Stir into sugar mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook about 2 minutes longer.
Cool and pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Use whites of eggs for meringue.

title: basic taco sauce
directions: Finely chop chile and tomatoes in food processor for 4 to 6 seconds.
Add garlic, onion (if using), salt, pepper and oregano. Mix well.
Allow to stand for 2 hours before using. Serve with either beef, chicken or cheese tacos.
Sauce will keep in refrigerator for about a week if sealed and if onion is not used. If onion is added, it is much more perishable.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to medium soft ball stage, 236°, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and chocolate squares.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: *To use canned peaches, drain juice from 20 ounce can; reduce sugar to 1/4 cup and use reserved juice for topping over batter.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, cracker crumbs, onions, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Heat shortening in large skillet until melted.
Cook meatballs over medium heat, stirring occasionally until done. Remove meatballs from skillet and keep warm.
Drain fat from skillet.
Mix cornstarch and brown sugar in same skillet; stir in reserved syrup, the vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Boil and stir 1 minute.	Add meatballs, pineapple and green pepper. Heat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Pour hot water over vegetables; drain.
Heat Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with canned fried onion rings during the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: fresh blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add eggs and beat well. Add mixed dry ingredients alternately with milk and lemon juice. Stir to combine.
Add and mix blueberries very carefully to avoid crushing.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Remove from oven and cut potatoes in halves.
Remove potato from peeling.
Mash potatoes well, adding butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Place peeling halves in pan.
Spoon potato mixture into peeling halves.
Top with cheese and put in oven until cheese is melted.

title: apple harvest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Generously grease (using 1 tablespoon solid shortening) and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan (nonstick finish pan, too).

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 325° preheated oven, about 20 minutes.
May be baked in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: petite caramel pecan rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Spread in the bottom of an ungreased 8 or 9-inch round pan.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Press line together.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix well and add nuts.
Dissolve soda in water and add last, mixing well.
Form dough into small rolls, wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 400° until brown (10 to 12 minutes).

title: mexican soup
directions: Saute chicken and onion in oil over medium-high heat until chicken is lightly brown.
In large pot, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: dump soup
directions: After browning first 3 ingredients, add the remaining items and then simmer 30 minutes.

title: best rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum for quality.
Now go ahead. Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again; it must be just right. To be sure rum is of the highest quality, pour one level cup of rum and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat, if necessary.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a large, fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of thugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, make sure the rum is of the highest quality by chugging another cup.
Open another quart if nethathery.
Add 2 arge leggs, 2 cups of fried druit and beat until high.
If druit gets stuck in beaters, pry it loose with a drewscriver.
Sample the rum, checking for toxicisicisicisity.
Next, sift 1/2 pint of lemon juice.
Fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add 1 babblespoon brown thugar, or whatever color you can find.
Wix mell.
Grease oven and turn cake pan to 350°.
Now pour the whole mess into the boven and ake.
Check the rum again and go to bed!

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix lettuce and spinach in equal parts, red onions and green peppers in serving bowl.
Fry bacon; drain and crumble and sprinkle over lettuce.
Add fresh mushrooms, sliced.
Add Parmesan cheese and mix all ingredients.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over low heat, melt butter and chocolate, stirring occasionally.
Remove saucepan from heat.
With wire whisk, beat in sugar, milk, flour, corn syrup, vanilla, salt and eggs until melted.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour chocolate mixture into pie crust.
Bake pie in preheated 350° oven 30 minutes or until filing is set and puffed.
Serve with ice cream, if you like.

title: tomato cheddar soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot at medium heat.
Add onions and saute until transparent (5 minutes).
Stir in flour; stir until smooth.
Add milk and tomatoes.
Gradually add chicken broth, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cheese can be added now or individually when serving soup.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: romanoff potatoes
directions: Pour cheese mix over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through.

title: granny's chuck wagon chili(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Brown meat in oil in a Dutch oven.
Remove meat; reserve drippings.
Saute 3/4 cup onion, green pepper and garlic in reserved drippings until tender.
Add meat and next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle with onion and cheese when ready to serve.

title: militello's chocolate decadence cake
directions: Line bottom of 9-inch springform pan with foil.
Butter foil and sides of pan.
In a large bowl, combine the melted butter, sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat well.
Blend in cocoa, flour and water; beat well.
Stir in the finely chopped pecans.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and milk in double boiler over hot water. Let cool and add to beaten eggs and sugar. Add melted butter and vanilla. Press into uncooked pastry shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken hash
directions: Mix the chicken with seasonings to taste and let sit. Brown the rice in 2 tablespoons butter. Add package seasoning. Add soup. May add broth as needed. Add chicken and cook on top of stove until rice is tender. Put in casserole. Bake until browned on top.

title: chocolate bits cookies
directions: Combine sifted dry ingredients into sugars and shortening to which egg and vanilla have been added.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: salsa dip
directions: Put cream cheese in center of plate and pour picante sauce over cream cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: poor man's dish
directions: Mix all together and set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° 1 hour, uncovered.

title: turkey
directions: Put onion in neck or chest.
Combine salt, Old Bay, pepper, garlic powder, oregano and oil and pour on turkey.
Soak overnight. Bake turkey 2 hours, then pour 2 beers around sides and bake 1 more hour, basting the last hour.
Boil potatoes; drain.
Take out turkey and put potatoes in basting sauce.
Add 1 cup water.
Bake potatoes about 1/2 hour at 500° or until dark brown or put potatoes in raw and cook until well done.

title: mother's homemade biscuit dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Cut in shortening with two knives or pastry blender. Add milk, using more if necessary to make a soft dough. Pat out 1/2-inch thick and cut into 1-inch squares, strips or diamonds. Drop into boiling chicken stock. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and salt together to 245° (candy thermometer) or until mixture is very thick.
Add butter until melts.
Add milk gradually to mixture, keeping mixture boiling at all times.
Stir constantly.
Cook rapidly to 242° or until a few drops form a firm ball when dropped in cold water.
The mixture will be very thick and sticks easily.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Wrap each piece in waxed paper.
Makes 7 dozen pieces.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown meats; drain.
Add cheese and meats together.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Spread on rye bread.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Thoroughly blend sour cream, cream cheese and milk.
Stir in onion, pepper and beef.

title: savory ham and potato bake
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk; cook until thick.
Add 1 1/2 cups (not all) cheese.
Stir until melted.
Toss in potatoes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(You may also use 3 loaf pans instead of tube pan.)

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onions; drain off fat.
Add catsup, sugar, dry mustard, salt and vinegar.
Stir.
Add beans.
Mix well.
Turn in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti squares
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper over meat; add onions, bread crumbs and milk.
Mix lightly.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan; press in.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender; drain, reserving liquid. Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Add enough water to potato liquid to make two cups.
Add to milk mixture along with potatoes, cheese, pepper and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted and soup is thoroughly heated.
Great "comfort food."

title: peachy chicken salad
directions: Lightly toss chicken, celery, grapes and peaches together. Mix mayonnaise and sour cream; pour over salad.
Add seasoning salt and mix gently.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve. Garnish with peaches and parsley. Serves 6.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix 1
cup applesauce with raspberry Jell-O, then mix 1 cup applesauce	with
lime
Jell-O.
(Mix
to
dissolve
each mixture in	separate bowl.) Place graham crackers flat in dish in rows and
layer 1 row raspberry Jell-O, then another layer of crackers, then
layer
of
lime
Jell-O filling.
Continue layers until about 5 inches high.
Cool in refrigerator until Jell-O sets. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar until dissolved, then combine with remaining ingredients.
Toss several times while marinating for 24 hours.

title: murray's house dressing(sweet and sour french)
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Store in covered container and refrigerate.

title: cereal muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% Bran.
Add Crisco and stir.
Add sugar, eggs, buttermilk, flour, soda and All Bran.
Mix well. Grease muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Keeps 6 to 7 weeks in refrigerator.
You may add dates or raisins.

title: every day casserole
directions: Saute ground meat, onions and pepper; place in casserole, then spread corn over meat mixture. Spread mashed potatoes over this, and sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook grits according to package directions.
Remove pot from heat and stir in cheese, margarine, eggs and Tabasco.
Continue stirring until well blended.
Pour into lightly greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes until lightly browned on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Stir well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Add carrots, nuts and pineapple. Stir well.
Spoon into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve cold, with or without butter.

title: mother's applesauce cake
directions: Using mixer, cream together butter, sugar and egg.
On wax paper, sift together flour, salt, baking soda, and cinnamon.
In a bowl, put raisins and nuts.
Sprinkle with a small amount of flour. Heat applesauce to lukewarm in microwave.
Combine creamed butter mixture, flour mixture and applesauce.
Mix well. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Drain vegetables; combine all ingredients.
Bake in covered casserole at 275° for five hours or in crock-pot.

title: southern fried chicken and milk gravy
directions: Soak chicken in
buttermilk
at
least	30 minutes.
In paper bag, put flour
and
seasonings.
Add chicken, close bag and shake vigorously.
(Secret
to
good browned fried chicken is to flour it twice.)	Remove	chicken to dry on waxed paper, then replace chicken in	flour
and shake again.
Use electric or
iron skillet.
Brown
chicken
on
both sides in hot oil. Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend sugar, onion, garlic, oil, salt and celery salt.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cut vegetables in bite size pieces.
Add dressing and toss several times.
Let stand 1 hour or longer.
Top with bacon bits.
The longer it sets, the better the flavor.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and serve with vegetables of your choice.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Slice chicken very thin.
While still partially frozen, stir together salad dressing, soy sauce, ginger and red pepper.
Set aside.
Heat oil in wok.
Stir-fry chicken for 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from wok.
Add a little more oil and stir-fry vegetables for about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add salad dressing.
Mix together. Simmer about 30 seconds.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Bone chicken and cut into large pieces.
Cut tortilla into 1-inch strips or squares.
Mix soups, milk, onion and salsa. Butter a large shallow baking dish.
Put 1 or 2 tablespoons chicken broth (or water) in bottom of baking dish.
Place a layer of tortillas in dish, then chicken, then soup mixture.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used, ending with soup mixture. Top with cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
This is important to allow the flavor to blend.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pretzel candy
directions: Place pretzels on wax paper.
Melt almond bark in a microwave-safe container or casserole on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until melted.
Spoon melted almond bark into center of pretzels.
Decorate with M&M's and let cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack into a loaf pan (oblong, 1-quart size).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion with salt and pepper until all liquid is out.
Cool.
Add cream of chicken soup, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Mix well.
Add margarine or butter (melted) to stuffing mix.

title: maple french toast
directions: Mix eggs, milk and vanilla.
Dip slices of bread into mixture and fry. Pour syrup over French toast and top with butter.

title: simple salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in large boiler.
Heat to boiling and turn down temperature to medium-low.
Cook two hours or until desired consistency.
(Longer cooking makes salsa thicker.)
Don't forget to stir often!

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 30 minutes.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Crumble cheese and add to other ingredients.
Superb!

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in salted water until thick, stirring.
Take off heat.
Add milk to beaten eggs to make 1 cup.
Stir into cheese and butter until melted.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Drop about 8 bell peppers in boiling water. Bring back to a boil for 5 minutes. Stuff with hamburger mixture. Cover with tomato or cheese and then cook for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: fried mozzarella
directions: Cut cheese
into
pieces.
Roll into flour; dip in egg. Roll in	bread crumbs, egg and bread crumbs again.
Fry in hot oil. Serve
with either spaghetti sauce or Ranch dressing for dipping.

title: pudding sauce
directions: Cook water, sugar, cornstarch and vinegar for 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Can be poured over plain cakes or other desserts as wanted.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt the stick of butter in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Put the graham cracker crumbs over the butter, patting it down until it forms a crust.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk over the crust.
Layer with chocolate chips, then coconut, then pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes so the coconut will become golden.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Melt margarine in milk.
Mix salt and sugar in a large bowl. Add milk mixture.
Stir and cool until luke warm.
Add yeast mixture and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough-enough to handle easy.
Store in a large greased bowl. Put aside in a warm place to rise.
Separate dough into three parts, roll out, and spread with margarine.
Cut into 2 inch wide strips.
Roll up, place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise and bake at 350 for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or done. Can be made in small cupcake pans, regular cupcake pan, loaf pan or Bundt pans.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Grate first 3 ingredients and add salt.
Mix well.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain.
Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed.
Boil 2 minutes and pour while hot over cabbage mixture.
Let cool well for at least 3 hours.
Put in containers. Have ample juice over top.
Freeze.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in pie shell.
Bake pie 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted into center of pie comes out clean.

title: yellow cake dessert
directions: Mix 1/2 cake mix, egg, water and oil together.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (makes thin layer cake).
Cool in pan.
Mix instant pudding and milk.
Add cream cheese and mix.
Pour over cake.
Add drained pineapple over cake; top with Cool Whip.

title: catsup relish
directions: Core tomatoes.
Strip off skin and quarter.
If necessary, rotate each tomato on a fork over heat until skin pops.
Chop finely the first 5 ingredients and add to 6 to 8-quart enamelled or stainless steel kettle.

title: easy russian tea
directions: Mix in bowl.
Makes 1 quart tea mix.
To serve, spoon 2 slightly rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture into mug and fill with boiling water.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Cover and chill.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Separate rolls and pat into ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes. Top with cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over crust, etc. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Bake.

title: oven "fried" potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In large plastic bag, empty onion soup mix and potatoes lightly sprayed with Pam. Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated. Empty into a shallow baking or roasting pan; discard bag. Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown. Garnish, if desired, with chopped or dry parsley flakes. Makes 8 servings.

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion in skillet until brown.
Add chili powder, cumin and salt; stir well.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.

title: italian-style cabbage rolls
directions: Lightly brown, stir and crumble sausage in skillet; drain drippings, leaving 2 tablespoons.
Saute green
pepper and celery with sausage 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Drain juice from tomatoes into sausage.
Add rice and salt.
Place cabbage leaves in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Spoon about 3 tablespoons of meat mixture in center of each leaf.
Package envelope-fashion. Spread drained tomatoes over cabbage and sprinkle with a little salt, sugar and oregano.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Shred lettuce; cover bottom of glass dish.
Add other 5 ingredients, layer at a time.
Spread on mayonnaise as frosting, then sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Stays fresh for a week.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: spanish rice(super healthy version)
directions: Use the sauce from my Spaghetti recipe, except add 1 tablespoon chili powder.
Use a 3 to 4-quart casserole dish. Place stone ground whole corn tortillas in the bottom of the casserole, then a layer of the meat sauce, then another layer of tortillas, etc.
Serves 6.

title: deluxe hash browns
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and let stand for 4 hours or more.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle with paprika and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Simmer until thick, stirring occasionally, about 2 hours.
Season with pepper.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: Rinse, drain and chop sauerkraut.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: italian smothered steak
directions: Simmer chopped onions in skillet with a little oil.
Beat together eggs, milk and 57 sauce.
Dredge serving sized portions of the tenderized round steak in egg, milk and 57 sauce mixture that has been beaten together, then dip into flour with salt and garlic salt dry mixture until coated.
Lay over simmering onions in skillet and brown on both sides.
Put in large baking pan with each slice flat.
Pour chopped stewed tomatoes over pieces and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until done.
Five minutes before done, put on slices of cheese and let melt; serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Bake full time.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Bring a large covered pot of water to a rapid boil.
Cook the pasta shells, uncovered, until al dente, then drain.
Rinse under cold water until cool; drain again.
Heat oil in a large saucepan. Add eggplant; cover and cook 3 minutes on medium heat.
Stir in salt, garlic, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons water.
Cover and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes, until the eggplant is almost tender. Add diced pepper and, if using dried herbs, add the dill and oregano.
Simmer a few minutes more, until the pepper is cooked but still has some crunch.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together; add egg.
Add the rest of the dry ingredients.
Divide the dough in half.
Roll into long sausages.
Roll in sugar then cut in 1-inch lengths, place on cookie sheet 1 inch apart.

title: creamy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown beef with onion in skillet.
Drain.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, milk and cornstarch; add cheese and seasoning. Combine with beef and onion.
Put into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Put on cookie sheet to prevent spills.

title: apple-berry crisp
directions: Heat oven 350 degrees. Spray 8 inch square baking dish. For filling combine ingredients until fruit is coated. Spoon into baking dish.

title: cherry crumble squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine dry cake mix, 1/4 cup melted butter and eggs; mix well.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch greased bottom of pan only.
Top with cherry pie filling.
In small mixing bowl, combine dry frosting mix with butter; sprinkle over cherries.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Serve as bars or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan; bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Double recipe and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: best salad
directions: Cut up lettuce for salad.
Add 3 boiled eggs, cut up.
Peel and core apple.
Add to lettuce.
Mix with enough Miracle Whip to moisten the salad.
You can serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine dressing and shake.
Toss salad before serving.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream, add garlic salt to taste. Add jalapeno, olives, onions and Cheddar.
Mix well.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up and place in sealed container overnight in refrigerator.
Slice into one-inch pieces.
Secure with toothpick if desired.
Serve with salsa.

title: white cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, baking powder and milk. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Mash pears and cream cheese together.
Add Dream Whip to mixture with the sauce.
Dissolve jello in 1/2 liquid.
Add remaining liquid and let cool.
Put all together and beat until mixture is smooth. Put in 8-inch square pan and let congeal.

title: poppy seed bars
directions: Melt butter; mix with graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan and pour on hot water. Mix sugar and flour; cut in butter and pat mixture on apples. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in casserole dish.
Then do topping by mixing next 3 ingredients.
Then place on top of potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 30 minutes or until easily speared with fork.

title: cooked french dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until mixture boils.
Let simmer a few minutes to cook the onion.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cape cod warmer(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in 4-cup glass measure.
Cook at High 5 to 6 minutes, Medium-low 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly. Strain into mug.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate sweet potatoes finely.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender and brown on top.
Amounts of sugar and butter may be halved.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, soda, cinnamon and salt and set aside. Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well.
Alternate dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine cucumber slices.
Remove peel.
Mix with onions and salt; let stand for 2 hours.
(Pickling cucumbers work well.) Heat vinegar and add sugar.
Let cool.
Drain excess liquid from standing cucumbers.
Pour sugar vinegar mixture over cucumber slices.
Mix together and pack in freezer containers.
Freeze. Allow to age for at least 2 weeks before defrosting and using.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites with a beater until stiff.
Spread crushed vanilla cookies on bottom of a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan (save enough crumbs for topping).
Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Spread over crumbs already in pan.
Spread 2 cans of pie filling on mixture (fruit).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts over fruit (optional).
Spread 2 cups whipped cream.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Keep refrigerated.

title: old-fashioned cornbread stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a medium skillet with nonstick spray.
Place cornbread in the casserole.
Then add onion mixture.
Drizzle with 1 cup of broth.
Gently toss.
If necessary, drizzle with remaining 1/2 cup of broth to moisten the bread; gently toss to mix well.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 4 layer chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add chopped pecans and flour.
Mix well and pat in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 125° to 150°.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and approximately 1/3 bowl of Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth.
Mix Jell-O instant chocolate pudding. Pour cream cheese mix on baked crusty layer.
Add the next layer of chocolate pudding.
Top with the remainder of Cool Whip.

title: bits of brickle cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mix all of it together with the brickle bits.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork dipped in milk. Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dorito dip
directions: Combine sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, lettuce and tomato. Refrigerate.
Serve cold.
Scoop up with Doritos.
(Salsa Rio are the best, but all varieties taste good.)

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Grease muffin pans.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl measure first seven ingredients (dry ingredients).
Stir with fork to mix.
In medium bowl beat eggs slightly.
Stir in zucchini and oil.
Stir this wet mixture all at once into the flour mixture, just until moistened.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake 25 minutes for 3 inch cups, 20 minutes for 2 1/2 inch cups or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Makes 12 to 18 muffins.

title: pecan pie
directions: Lightly beat eggs.
Add Karo and brown sugar.
Mix only until smooth.
Add salt, melted margarine, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch deep-dish pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet which has been heated in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and continue cooking for another 25 minutes or until firm.

title: aunt marianne's green bean frittata
directions: In a bowl, place well drained green beans.
Add bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
In a separate bowl, beat 3 eggs.
Pour eggs over green bean mixture, tossing to mix well.

title: weekend chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, eggs, pickles and salt.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce.
Trim with olives.
Serves 8.

title: all sorts goodies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar (optional). With a pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Store in airtight, covered, container.
Keeps for months in refrigerator.
You may use this mixture for hot biscuits, pancakes, waffles, dumplings, etc.
Use 1/3 cup of milk for every cup of mixture.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef
with onion and green pepper in large Dutch oven.
Drain
fat and return meat mixture to Dutch oven. Add garlic salt
and
next
4 ingredients.
Stir well.	Cover. Reduce heat.
Simmer
minutes.
Cook macaroni according to package directions	(omit salt).
Drain.
Add to meat mixture. Stir well. Spoon
into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top evenly
with pepperoni.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20
minutes. Top
with
cheese.	Bake
uncovered
minutes. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: geneva's goulosh
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Put into big pot and add tomatoes and juice.
Bring to boil.
Cook spaghetti in another pan, then add
to tomato and beef mixture.	Add catsup, sauce, sugar and garlic
salt.
Bring to boil, then let simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour
into
oblong pan;
shred cheese on top.
Place in oven for about 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: *Add 1 tbsp. vinegar to 1 cup milk or use buttermilk.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° glass).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine. Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients in order.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Chill, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: cheese-potato bake
directions: Mix (except for a little chopped green onion saved) all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cook for 2 hours in 350° oven.
Sprinkle some of the chopped green onion on top and serve.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: Roll chicken in oil to coat.
Place in baking dish, salt and pepper; sprinkle on garlic.
Squeeze 1/2 lemon over chicken.
Slice remaining lemon.
Place on each piece of chicken.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Turn and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Spoon pan juices over chicken before serving.
Serves 4.

title: old fashioned holiday pumpkin bread
directions: *I recommend either of these!

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is still hot, punch holes all over with a toothpick.
Blend cream of coconut and condensed milk.
Spoon over cake while still warm.
Cool completely and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble into small pieces.
Combine broccoli, bacon, onion and raisins in large bowl.
Blend together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Mix well and let stand at least 3 hours before serving.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in shaker or put in blender.

title: teriyaki shish kebabs
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; toss with beef.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain beef, reserving marinade.
Thread meat, pineapple and vegetables alternately on long skewers.
Grill over hot coals for 15 to 20 minutes, turning often or until meat reaches desired doneness and vegetables are tender.
Simmer the marinade in a small saucepan over low heat for 15 minutes.
Remove meat and vegetables from skewers; serve with marinade.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: jean's macaroni surprise(country:  u. s. a.)
directions: Cook macaroni until almost done.
Drain.
Put into a baking pan.
Add Spam, peas, soups and cheese (if desired).
Pour milk into one can and rinse them into another can; rinse that can. Pour into a baking pan.
Use one can milk for every two cans of soup.
Bake at 350° until top is light brown.
Mixture before baking should appear loose.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, beating mixtures after each egg.
Add gradually flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well. Fold in carrots.
Bake in greased rectangular pan at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients; put into a greased 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° with the lid on.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Salt chicken and place in oblong baking dish.
Combine
sour
cream, soup and sherry; pour over chicken. Sprinkle
generously
with paprika.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Top with almonds.
Serve with rice, seasoned with ginger and more almonds.
Serves 8.

title: trout scollop
directions: Steam or boil trout.
Remove bones and skin.
Place flakes of fish in a deep dish.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
Pour white sauce over fish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken pot pie casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine next 4 ingredients to make mixture and pour over chicken. To make the top, stir together Bisquick, milk and butter.
Pour on top of chicken mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Heat beans and water to boiling; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Stir in pork, onion, garlic, pepper sauce and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until beans are tender (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Do not boil or beans will burst.

title: sloppy joe pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, water and seasoning mix.
Heat meat mixture until hot and bubbly.
Reduce heat and simmer, separate biscuit, flatten, dip in milk, then cornmeal.
Spread in pie dish, around sides, then the bottom.
Biscuits will cook together to form crust. Sprinkle half of cheese on bottom and pour beef mixture on biscuits.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over top of mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool mixture.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Let cake cool.
Then cut cake in half horizontally. Slice ice cream into about 1/2-inch slices.
Cover 1st layer of cake with ice cream slices.
Place 2nd cake layer on top of ice cream.
Frost top of cake with whip cream.
Freeze for 2 hours. Top with hot fudge, nuts and cherries before serving.

title: chow mein
directions: Heat in skillet the oil, soy sauce and garlic.
Saute in oil mixture the mushrooms, onion and celery.
Add Chinese vegetables (bean sprouts, snow pea pods, bamboo shoots, ect.).
Thicken with cornstarch, water and molasses.
Serve on rice or chow mein noodles.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: western rice
directions: Brown meat in skillet, stirring frequently.
Drain any excess grease.
Stir in onion soup mix, water, rice, peas and tomatoes. Simmer in covered skillet until rice is tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Add a small amount of water or tomato juice if it becomes dry.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat until it melts or top each individual serving with cheese as it is served.
Serve 4 to 6.

title: apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil until creamy.
Add flour slowly.
Batter will be quite stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Fill muffin cups with batter, about 1/2 full.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Yield: Approximately 36 muffins.

title: avocado diplubbock, texas
directions: Gradually add the avocado to the cream cheese, blending until smooth.
Add lemon juice, onion, salt and worchester sauce.
Mix well.
Serve with potato chips.

title: flour tortilla
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar.
Mix the melted butter/margarine in.
Add milk until smooth.
If it is too dry, not a stiff dough, add enough water/milk to make a dough.
Cut off about a handful to cook.
Roll flat on a floured surface.
Cook on a hot ungreased pan.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Knead, cover and let rise 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onions, cut into 1/2-inch slices and separate into rings. Place in a plastic or paper bag and add 1 cup flour. Shake bag until onions are coated. Combine remaining 1 1/4 cups flour, baking powder and

next 4 ingredients; stir in egg yolks, mixing well. Beat egg whites at room temperature until stiff peaks form. Fold into batter. Dip onion rings into batter. Pour oil to depth of 2-inches into a Dutch oven; heat to 375°. Fry, turning once, until golden brown. Drain on paper towels and serve immediately. Yield: 4 servings.

title: five minute chocolate pudding(diet)
directions: In a small dish, put cold water.
Sprinkle gelatine over water to soften.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved and clear. In small mixing bowl, put cocoa and Equal.
Pour in cream and vanilla.
Beat until thick and frothy.
Pour in gelatine and mix well.
Spoon into dishes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and put in casserole dish.
Add gravy and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oat cakes
directions: Everything else is the same.

title: stuffed tomato potato salad
directions: Cut tomatoes in halves; scoop out centers to make cups. Strain pulp to remove excess liquid; reserve pulp.
Pat inside of tomato cups with paper towels to dry.
Combine reserved tomato pulp, potato, carrot, cottage cheese, parsley and salt.
Spoon mixture into tomato cup.
Chill.
Makes 8 stuffed shells, about 40 calories each.

title: fern's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar gradually. Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Cream well.
Add flour sifted with baking powder.
Mix well. Chill for 10 minutes. Roll out on floured surface. Cut into desired shapes.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
May be frosted or decorated with colored sugar. Yields 3 dozen large cookies.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Saute chicken in oil until lightly browned.
Add garlic and vegetables and stir fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add bouillon, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, ginger and pineapple with juice.
Bring to full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to instructions on box.
Drain spinach and mix with rest of ingredients.
Pour into buttered quiche dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "little" quiche
directions: Mix and chill cream cheese, oleo and flour.
Roll into 24 balls.
Press into tassie cups.
Combine bacon, ham, onion and Swiss cheese.
Place equal amounts of mixture into cups.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour 2 teaspoons of mixture over filled cups. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Stir together first 3 ingredients. Press mixture into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove to a wire rack and cool completely. Beat cream cheese and cream of coconut at medium speed of an electric beater until smooth. Add pudding mix, beating until blended. Stir in coconut. Fold in whipped topping. Spread cheese mixture evenly into prepared crust. Cover and chill 2 hours or until set. Beat whipping cream with an electric beater until soft peaks form. Spread evenly over pie. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow	Solomon's prescription for a good boy, Proverbs 23:14. Bake
in
a large tube pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: tortellini with tomato and cream sauce(serves 8 people)
directions: Briefly saute vegetables in melted butter.
Add tomatoes with juice and seasonings.
Add basil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and puree.
Return to pot; bring to simmer.
Add cream and cook one minute.
This sauce is rich.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in refrigerator overnight. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours or until tender. Thicken gravy with cornstarch.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: orange delicious
directions: Mix in blender, adding ice slowly.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Add and combine rest of ingredients together and pour into a 9 X 13 inch pan.
Place in freezer until frozen.
Let thaw a few minutes before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread on bottom of rectangular casserole dish.
Add hamburg and press lightly into cream mixture.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Top off with shredded cheese. Serve cold with nacho chips.

title: carrot ginger soup
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 4 minutes.
Peel and cut into small pieces.
Saute onions, garlic and carrots in vegetable oil.
Add salt.
Cook 30 minutes until tender.
Add cold water and sweet potatoes.
Add ginger (pouch), orange zest and orange juice.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove ginger.
Puree or mash if too thick.
Add a little water.
Enough for 8 people.

title: spicy mexican cocktail
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients, except vodka and celery.
Cover and cook over medium heat until heated through. Stir in vodka, if desired.
Serve in mugs with celery stick stirrers.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and season to taste.
Shape into tiny meat balls.
Into saucepan, pour contents of 8 ounce can of tomato spaghetti sauce.
Place balls in sauce and simmer about 10 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
To serve, just heat in chafing dish at buffet table.
Supply cocktail picks.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pour milk over sugar and oleo.
Cool.
Add dissolved yeast. Add 8 cups flour, one at a time; let rise double.
Add 1 cup flour and other ingredients.
Let rise double.
Punch down and store in refrigerator in a covered container.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: spinach squares
directions: Squeeze out as much moisture from spinach as possible.
Set aside.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms; cook, stirring, until soft.
In bowl, beat eggs lightly; stir in onion mixture, bread crumbs, soup, 2 tablespoons cheese, pepper, basil, oregano and spinach.
Pour into well greased 9-inch square baking pan; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Serve warm; or let cool, cover, refrigerate and serve cold.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Wash wings.
Split at each joint and discard tips.
Deep fry at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes, until crispy.
Drain well.

title: b.j.'s cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onions, garlic and dry seasonings together.
Add chopped smoke turkey, if desired.
Mix well. Using oil, coat hands and form a ball with cream cheese and first mixture.
Pour finely crushed pecans on 1 sheet of wax paper and spread them out.
(Make sure oil is coated on cheese ball and roll cheese ball over pecans.)
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: marshmallow delights(cinnamon rolls)
directions: Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Dip each marshmallow into melted margarine and roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place one marshmallow on each triangle and pinch dough around marshmallow, sealing all edges.
Dip tops of dough into remaining margarine and cinnamon/sugar mixture.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots and raisins; set aside.
Mix yogurt and lemon juice.
Stir sauce into carrot-raisin mixture.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: fudge 5 pounds
directions: Mix and stir sugar, margarine and milk. Boil exactly 9 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in chips and marshmallow cream. Pour into buttered pan. Refrigerate.

title: ron militello's italian spaghetti
directions: Set out a large saucepot having a tight fitting cover.
Heat the olive oil in the saucepot.
Add onion and cook until lightly browned.
Add meat to the saucepot and cook, turning occasionally until browned.
Remove and slice the pork from the bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Return the pork to the saucepot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over very low heat.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake cake as directed in square baking dish. When cool, punch holes all in cake with butter knife.
Mix Jell-O as directed; pour all into holes of cake.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Spread whipped topping on cake and top with halved strawberries.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook gently until potatoes are tender.
Put aside.
Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk; add to stock.
Put in blender. Add egg and heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: imitation mushrooms
directions: Mix soup, eggs and well crumbled crackers together.
Drop by a teaspoon into hot frying grease, flattening the mixture slightly. Fry until brown and drain on paper towels.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.
Chill and garnish just before serving with the bacon.
Very good!

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into pieces.
Brown with onions, salt and pepper.
Add water after it's browned and put to simmer for 1/2 hour or so.
Put in roaster.
Add 2 cans mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 can water; mix well.
Put in 350° oven for about 1 hour or so.
About 1/2 hour before serving, add 1 1/2 cups sour cream and mix well.
Serve over white rice or mashed potatoes.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cream the butter. Beat in cream, a little at a time, until mixture is well combined. Beat in Parmesan cheese. Set aside until at room temperature.
Pour over cooked fettucine.

title: cookies and cream salad
directions: Make the vanilla pudding with milk and instant pudding. Before pudding sets, add Cool Whip and stir until blended.
Add marshmallows.
Break Oreo cookies into fourths and gently stir in. Refrigerate.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots (sliced 1/4-inch thick) until tender.
Cool before putting into sauce.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over carrots.
Chopped onions and green peppers may be added if desired.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
In casserole, put Fritos on bottom, then layer with chili, onion, con carne, ground beef, then cheese. Repeat this until casserole is full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until casserole is hot and cheese is melted.

title: tangy buffet meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Shape to form 1 inch balls, bake on rack in a shallow baking pan at 400° for 15-17 minutes.

title: tuna and rice
directions: Saute green onions.
Add chopped eggs and drained tuna.
Stir in soup and milk.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Cover over rice.

title: drop dumplings or puffy
directions: Beat egg; add milk.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to egg and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling liquid (chicken or beef broth).
Cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb strawberry jam
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water for 15 minutes on medium-hot heat, boiling.
Add strawberry jello and mix well with rhubarb mixture.
Makes 2 pints.
Can be put in refrigerator and kept for several days.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter.
Place chicken in dish, fully boned and broken in pieces.
Mix cream soups and sour cream in a bowl.
Then spread over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing crumbs evenly over cream soup mixture.
Mix butter and chicken broth; drizzle over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: diabetic grape jelly
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup grape juice and set aside. Combine all other ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Add dissolved gelatine to mixture and boil 2 minutes.
Pour into glasses and keep in refrigerator or freezer.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.

title: mexican party soup
directions: Heat butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Saute carrots and celery until tender.
Add soup, milk, picante sauce and cumin.
Stir until smooth.
Heat until hot, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil!
Add cheeses and stir until melted.
Yields 5 cups.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili egg puff
directions: Beat the eggs until light.
Add the flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and melted butter, blending smoothly.
Stir in the chiles.
Pour mixture into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great as a main course, or cut into small squares as appetizers.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Cook cake mix in 3 layers.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add fruit and mix.
Pour into mold.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Mix together and put into a buttered and floured pan (8 x 8-inch). Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add orange juice, pineapple and oranges.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Chill until firm.

title: orange coffee cake
directions: Dip biscuits in melted margarine, then in sugar-orange mixture.
Arrange in pie plate and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Arrange on a round plate and serve with a good cup of coffee.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets (skins) until done.
Let cool; do not peel.
Cut into wedges or cubes.
In a separate bowl, mix the Hidden Valley Ranch dressing, buttermilk and mayonnaise.
Chill for 30 minutes or more.
Toss the dressing mixture over the potatoes; stir carefully.
Sprinkle the seasoning over the potatoes; stir carefully.
Chill before serving.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking pan.
Combine butter, honey, mustard and curry powder.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste while cooking with mixture in pan.

title: "up-to-date" potato pancakes
directions: Mix together pancake mix and salt. Stir in milk and beaten eggs. Lightly stir in potato, onion and melted shortening.
Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake onto hot, lightly greased griddle. Bake to a golden brown, turning only once.
Makes 14 to 16 pancakes.

title: rye bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine rye flour, molasses, shortening and salt.
Add boiling water and blend well.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and white flour to make soft dough.
Put on floured surface; cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and satiny (about 10 minutes).
Put dough in a lightly greased bowl.
Cover and let rise.
When doubled in size, punch down and let rise again.
Divide into 4 balls and let rest until doubled in size.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with caraway seed, if desired.
Bake in 4 large pie tins at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: summer squash
directions: Combine and cook until done.

title: dill pickle soup
directions: Add onion to butter and saute until tender; add wine and cook until liquid almost evaporates.
Stir in flour but do not brown.
Combine water and pickle juice and whisk into mixture all at once.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly until soup thickens.
Add pickles and dill weed.
Stir in cream if lighter color is desired.
Season with poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Garnish with diced dill pickles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda. Stir in the walnuts and orange peel.
Mix egg, orange juice and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: apricot date bars
directions: Cook dates, apricots, 1/3 cup brown sugar and water until thickens.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Next, blend together and hold shortening and 1 cup brown sugar.
Sift and mix flour and soda.
Mix in oatmeal and vanilla to flour and soda.
Work these into sugar mixture, then spread 1/2 oatmeal crumb mixture into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add fruit mixture and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ultimate choco chip cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add nuts. Alternately add bananas and flour.
Blend.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a loaf pan or for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or until turns loose from edge of pan.

title: green bean salad
directions: Heat vinegar, water, sugar and oil. Put veggies in shallow dish and pour hot vinegar dressing over them. Refrigerate. Must do ahead.

title: fresh apple-nut bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine next 7 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: tomato soup to can
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions and peppers until tender.
Run this mixture through colander to make juice.
Take out 2 pints of juice and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour this mixture back in the juice and heat to boiling, stirring to avoid sticking.
Put soup in jars.
Hot water bath pints 12 minutes and quarts 24 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together in a bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Add the shortening, 1/3 cup buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Beat these ingredients vigorously for about 2 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and unbeaten eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes; fold in the chopped nuts. Pour batter into prepared pans, either 2 round pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or check at 25 minutes for test.
Cool, then frost layers and top.

title: tomato and bean curd soup
directions: Rinse and wipe dry the bean curd; dice.
Rinse tomatoes and cut into chunks.
Saute ginger slice.
Fry in tomatoes.
Add some water, bring to a boil, then add in diced bean curd.
Boil until ingredients are done and soup thickens.
Stir in seasonings. Remove quickly from stove.
Blend in egg.
Sprinkle diced spring onion on top and it's ready to serve.

title: lemon flavored shake
directions: Put milk and ice cream (and malt balls) in blender.
Set the blender to chop.
Stop the blender when almost done to squeeze the lemon into the blender.
When done, drink and enjoy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: wild tasty cheese ball
directions: Mix raisins, 1/3 cup peanuts, green onions and cream cheese. Form into a ball.
Roll ball in remaining 1/4 cup peanuts.
Chill. Serve with crackers and pour chutney on cheese ball immediately prior to serving.

title: mom's cookies
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add water to the raisins and boil for 5 minutes or until decreased to 1/2 cup of water. Cream the shortening and sugar and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, nuts and cooled raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: angel hair delite
directions: Prepare pasta according to package.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Combine onion and green pepper with all other ingredients except pasta.
Place in microwave and cook on High for 20 minutes.

title: our favorite potatoes
directions: Place thinly sliced (peeled or not) potatoes in casserole coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Skin onion and slice.
Place onion ringlets on top of potatoes.
Slice margarine into about 8 pats and arrange over potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle generously with pepper and seasoned salt.

title: sausage balls
directions: Remove casing from sausage.
Cook in skillet.
Drain fat. Cool in large bowl.
Add cheese, Bisquick and water.
Mix with fork, just until blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into pizza pan.
Bake until dough begins to brown on top only.
Do not cook until crunchy.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut top from pumpernickel round bread.
Hollow out loaf and cube insides.
Fill with dip.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place slices of bread on bottom glass Pyrex baking dish. Butter bread.
Layer sausage, then cheese.
Make mixture of eggs and milk; stir.
Pour over casserole.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple spice muffin
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease bottoms only of muffin tin. Combine flour, germ, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder, 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon and salt.
Stir in apple.
In another bowl, combine milk, oil, egg whipped and milk.
Add to dry ingredients until just moistened.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, nuts and margarine.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: baked hominy
directions: Saute onion in butter; add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well. Drain hominy and add to mix.
Put into baking dish.
Cover with crushed Fritos.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jack's pasta and oil
directions: Bring oil and water to a boil.
Saute 1 thin sliced clove of garlic until almost brown.
Add fresh parsley, mix and pour over al dente pasta.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Debone and keep broth.
Beat eggs and water.
Add flour.
Separate into two parts.
Knead part on floured board until springy.
Roll out and cut into thin strips.
Do same with the other half.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.
Turn down and simmer until dumplings sink to the bottom, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and continue cooking for 10 minutes more.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix meal vinegar, sugar, eggs. flour, vanilla and butter together until well blended. Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: stephanie's snack bars
directions: Use your own sugar cookie recipe.
This one is for lots of handling by the youngest cook.

title: banana-raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray and set aside.
Into small mixing bowl sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion in saucepan.
Cook in water over medium heat about 20 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Mash and add all other ingredients.
Place in baking dish and cover top with 1 cup grated American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Shred carrots into mixing bowl.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and raisins to mix.

title: reeses' balls
directions: Dip balls into mixture.
Cool on wax paper.
You can use toothpicks to dip the balls in chocolate.
Make the balls about the size of chocolate covered cherries.

title: poppy seed bread or cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and beat 4 minutes. Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 1 tube/Bundt pan. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp seafood chowder
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until mashable.
Fry bacon and green pepper.
Drain, and add all ingredients together.
Do not boil after adding the half and half.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix cool whip, cream cheese, and sugar together.
Make pudding by directions on box.
Crush cookies and mix with butter.
Put layer of cookie mixture on bottom, then layer of pudding.
Then layer of cool whip mixture, top with cookies and refrigerate.

title: gospel chicken
directions: Salt chicken pieces and place on top of uncooked rice, butter and water in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with soups and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Combine
margarine, water, caramels in pan stir until completely melted.
Then add rest of ingredients into pan.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 325 degrees until crust is brown.

title: fish stew
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onion and garlic about 5 minutes, stirring often until onion is tender.
Stir in chili powder, cook 2 minutes stirring often.
Stir in broth and chilies.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, pepper, shrimp and fish.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork and shrimp are heated through.
Gradually stir in yogurt and heat just until hot (do not boil).
