title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and allow to cool.
Add cream (do not whip, just stir in) and chill in refrigerator until mushy.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Put into molds or dish and refrigerate until set.

title: french cherry pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Whip the heavy cream.
(Note: Whipped cream should be stiff.)
Fold cream cheese mixture into whipped cream. Spread this in baked pie shell.

title: ham and sweets casserole
directions: In a frying pan, brown ham.
Place ham in a large casserole. Slice the sweet potatoes over it.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Add water to drippings in the frying pan, heat and blend.
Pour 1/2 over sweet potatoes.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally with remaining liquid.
Remove cover.
Brown for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place in mixed vegetables next, if desired.
Mix chicken soup and broth together. Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and margarine together. Spoon over chicken mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Grease jelly roll pan; line with greased wax paper.
Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin, cinnamon, soda and flour.
Spread in pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn in clean dish towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll up in towel, wax and all.
Put in refrigerator.
Cool 1 1/2 hours.

title: cold bread pudding
directions: Crumble biscuit crumbs into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Mix eggs and milk real well; add vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix again. Put 1/2 cup of sugar and raisins (if you want) over crumbs.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Let set in refrigerator for 30 minutes to soak up bread crumbs, then bake at about 375° for 30 minutes.

title: best and easy sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well. Blend in oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli potato caesar salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Wash potatoes.

Cook in enough boiling water to cover. Cook 18 to 20 minutes, or until tender; drain and cool slightly. Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices and place in a large bowl. Pour sour cream mixture over potatoes and toss gently.
Arrange broccoli in a vegetable steamer over boiling water; cover and steam 4 to 5 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Drain.
Add broccoli, red pepper, Parmesan cheese and parsley to potato mixture; stir gently.
Yield:
5 cups (79 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 325° about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, milk, salt, oatmeal, eggs, 1 cup onion, chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder and black pepper well with hands.
Make into walnut size balls.
Place in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Mix ketchup, liquid smoke, 1/2 cup onion, brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder and spoon over balls.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oatmeal, well.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: gumdrop coconut cookies(another christmas favorite of the seiter children)
directions: Cream sugar and butter or shortening.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Continue beating.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: grilled fish
directions: Mix enough butter and Italian dressing to cover fish.
Mix together and spread on foil.
Put fish on and turn over; sprinkle with Tony's, Cavender's and oregano.
Grill until cooked.
When fish flakes, it's cooked.

title: cauliflower, carrot and broccoli casserole
directions: Place cauliflower head in center of 15-inch glass dish. Arrange cut up vegetables around outside.
Pour butter over vegetables.
Sprinkle on garlic salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap; turn back an edge to vent.
Microwave on High for 17 to 19 minutes.
Let stand covered for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole.
Blend spinach, melted butter, cream cheese and lemon juice together.
Place artichokes on bottom of casserole.
Add spinach mixture.
Top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage, stirring to separate into small pieces.
Pour off any drippings in excess of 1/4 cup.
Add cabbage, water, salt and pepper to sausage.
Cover; simmer only until cabbage is crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.

title: crisp chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, mayonnaise, celery and onions into mixing bowl. Add 1 cup corn flake crumbs, soup and water chestnuts. Place in 2-quart casserole. Melt oleo. Add remaining 1 cup crumbs. Mix well and use as topping for casserole. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until boiling.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with paprika and more cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: crumb-topped salmon
directions: In a bowl, combine the first eight ingredients; set aside. Pat salmon dry. Place skin side down, in a 13 x 9 baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Spritz salmon with butter-flavored spray; cover with crumb mixture. Spritz crumbs with butter-flavored spray. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 - 20 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.

title: hash 'n cheese grill
directions: Mix hash, ketchup, onion, parsley flakes and oregano.
Spread on muffin halves.
Top with cheese strips.
Set oven control at boil and/or 550°.
Boil 8 to 10-inches from heat until cheese is melted and hash mixture is bubbly and hot.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill for one hour.
Roll into small balls and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix together with hands and put in muffin pans.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° to 400°.
Makes 12.

title: corn fritters made with fresh corn
directions: Scrape corn.
Add egg yolk, flour and salt.
Whip until stiff, but not dry, the egg white.
Fold the corn mixture into it.
Saute as pancakes in oil or butter until light brown and fluffy.
Do not overcook!

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Hollow out Hawaiian bread loaf, saving bread carved out for dippers.
Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into hollow bread and wrap loosely with foil.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with bread dippers and large-sized Fritos.

title: taco salad delight
directions: Cook hamburger; drain well and cool.
Mix shredded lettuce. Cut up tomatoes and remove seeds.
Add shredded cheese.
When ready to serve, add salad dressing and crushed tortilla chips. Mix well and serve.

title: quick fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together evaporated milk, sugar and salt; bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat and stir constantly; simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate and vanilla; beat with spoon until completely blended. Turn into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool completely. Cut into squares. Cover tightly with transparent plastic film and store in refrigerator.

title: sly
directions: Mix dough for small cookie sheet.
Cover bottom and pour mixture on it.
Cover with another piece of dough.
Seal sides together, then puncture little holes with fork here and there to let out steam.
Bake same as pie cooked when golden brown.
Cut in squares.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour 1/2 of the batter in the pan.
Grate 1/2 pound cheese and 2 hot peppers, chopped.
Sprinkle on batter in pan and pour remaining batter on top.	Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: aunt rose's hickory nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix corn syrup, brown sugar, salt, melted butter and vanilla.
Beat eggs slightly and mix in.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake about 45 minutes until knife inserted about halfway to middle of pie comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Empty tomatoes into 2-quart saucepan.
Add tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, green pepper, celery and green onion.
Cook covered on medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add spices and seasoning and cook another 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch to 1/2 cup water.
Stir.
Then stir into tomato mixture to thicken.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.

title: mussels in garlic butter
directions: Combine butter with lemon juice, lemon peel, parsley, garlic and onions; season to taste with pepper.
Blend butter-herb mixture in food processor or electric blender until well blended. Arrange mussels in their shell halves, on large baking dish. Spread each mussel with some butter herb mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 10 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash and chill lettuce.
Rub salad bowl with garlic.
Add salt and pepper.
Break in one egg.
Squeeze juice from lemons into bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine oil and Worcestershire; add to salad bowl.
Place chilled lettuce in bowl and mix.
Add croutons, cheese and anchovies, if desired.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix; put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat egg slightly in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients except blueberries, just until moistened.
Fold blueberries into batter. Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, milk, salt and margarine. Heat slowly and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let stand until firm, about 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad with fresh tomato and basil sauce
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
In the meantime, cut up fresh tomatoes into eighths and saute garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes to olive oil and garlic.
Add dried spices, herbs and hot pepper.
Add green peppers and fresh basil.
Cook on low for about 15 minutes, stirring often.
Put cooked pasta in bowl; coat with olive oil and add hot pasta sauce, removing hot pepper first.
Serve at once and top with freshly grated Romano cheese.
If you add pine nuts, add them to pasta sauce at the last minute.

title: double-quick meat loaf and gravy duet
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
On a 22 to 24-inch strip of heavy-duty aluminum foil, mix beef and onion soup; mix thoroughly, being careful not to tear foil.
Form into loaf and pour undiluted cream of mushroom soup over loaf.
Wrap loosely in foil.
Place on baking sheet.
As this loaf bakes, the meat juices combine with the mushroom soup to make a wonderful brown gravy to serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: isolated m chicken
directions: Put ham pieces in bottom of pan.
Place chicken on top of ham. Put bacon slices on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together and pour over chicken. Bake, covered, at 300° for 3 hours.
Stir and serve over rice.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces and cook in salted water until done.
Mix flour and butter and cook together; add milk.
Salt and pepper.
Add this mixture to cabbage.
Cook slow, about 3 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put pecans in pie shell.
Mix other ingredients together well and pour pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well. Bake 20 minutes in a moderate oven at 350° in buttered baking dish with bread crumbs at the top and bottom.
If desired, fruit may be added to the rice in layers.

title: mexican rice pudding(serves 6)
directions: To briskly boiling water, add the teaspoon of salt and rice. Cook for 15 minutes.
Drain and add rice to hot milk.
Add stick cinnamon and cook until rice is tender, about 1/2 hour.
Stir in sugar.
Remove pudding from heat.
Take out cinnamon and add beaten egg yolks, mixed with the cold milk.
Return to heat and cook until thick, approximately 5 minutes longer.
Pour pudding into buttered serving dish and sprinkle top with powdered cinnamon.
(Raisins may be added.)

title: lo-cal mexican fried chicken
directions: Mix V-8 juice and Tabasco sauce.
Marinate chicken in this for 3 hours in refrigerator, then 1/2 hour at room temperature.
Drain and throw away the marinade.
Put cornflake crumbs and all seasonings in plastic bag.
Shake 1 piece at a time and place in a shallow baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle any leftover coating on chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jello strawberry shortcake
directions: In long dish, break angel food cake in small pieces.
Mix jello with 2 cups hot water and 2 cups cold water and frozen strawberries.
Mix well.
Pour over angel food cake.
Refrigerate until set, then put Cool Whip on top.

title: kay's pickles
directions: Spread cream cheese on a slice of corned beef.
Dry pickles with paper towel.
Wrap beef and cream cheese around pickle and slice into bite size pieces.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/2 cup more flour.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: tortilla bites
directions: Mix cream cheese, chilies, olives and green onions in bowl. Spread mixture evenly onto flour tortilla.
Roll up and chill. Slice before serving.
Serve with salsa.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done, but not mushy.
Let cool completely and skin.
Dice.
Add diced eggs and sweet pickles.
Mix together Miracle Whip, mustard, sugar, and pickle juice.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
If not enough dressing, mix a little more.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender, stir in tomatoes and pizza sauce mix.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pizza dough as directed on box.
With fingers greased, press onto bottom and half way up sides of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with half of Mozzarella cheese, then cheese slices and 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: spinach fettuccine
directions: Cut boiled chicken breast in strips and mix with fettuccine and mushrooms.
Pour in a mixer the cream cheese, sour cream, broth (1 cup approximately) and other liquids; mix very well.

title: company chuck roast
directions: Wrap meat in foil to retain the roast's natural juices.
Place chuck roast in center of large piece of aluminum foil in a roasting pan.
Brush meat with steak sauce and sprinkle onion soup mix over it.
Spread with mushroom soup.
Wrap loosely in foil and roast at 350° for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: island punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl; mix well.
Serve over ice cubes if desired.

title: venison casserole
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Mix together flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Coat meat with seasoned flour and brown on both sides in hot fat.
Place in greased casserole dish and add the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: smoky cheese balls
directions: Let cream cheese, shredded cheese and margarine/butter set at room temperature to soften.
With a mixer, blend milk and steak sauce until fluffy.
Cover; chill in refrigerator no less than 4 hours.
Shape mixture into balls; roll in nuts.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers; slice and spread.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: heavenly pound cake
directions: Add eggs, oil and water to cake mix.
After mixing well, add instant pudding.
Bake in tube pan 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
(Do not remove skins.) Boil in salted water for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Scoop out center, leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Mash scooped out part and season with chopped onion, minced pepper, salt and pepper.
Add crumbled bacon and butter.
Fill shells; sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter gradually, adding next 4 ingredients.
Cool dough until firm.
Form walnut-sized balls.
Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 20 minutes or until lightly brown on bottom.
Dip hot cookies in mixture of 1 cup powdered sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Beat or cream eggs, sugar and salt until creamy and lemon colored. Add soft butter or margarine. Beat well.
Add the flour. Blend well. Add milk.
Mix well, then fold in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining coconut on top. Bake in slow oven at 325° about 60 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add pineapple juice (should be 3 1/2 cups total liquid, if not, add a little water), mix well and add fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate and let set.

title: beef 'n broccoli stir-fry
directions: Blend steak sauce, soy sauce and garlic.
In large bowl, pour marinade over steak.
Chill for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Remove steak from marinade; reserve marinade.
In large lightly oiled skillet over medium-high heat, stir-fry beef for 3 to 4 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Remove steak with slotted spoon.
Keep warm.
In the same skillet, heat vegetables and reserved marinade to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in beef.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: salt dough(for kids)
directions: This recipe has been passed down in the Carollo family for decades.
Used as a snack or cooked together with fried potatoes, there is no match to their flavor.

title: sticky buns
directions: Combine sugar, butter and one tablespoon water in 8-inch glass baking dish.
Cook uncovered in microwave at 70% power for 2 minutes or until butter melts.
Stir mixture and spread over bottom of dish.
Sprinkle nuts on top of sugar and place biscuits on top of nuts.
Bake uncovered at 70% power for 4 to 5 minutes or until biscuits are firm and no longer doughy.
Let stand about 2 minutes.
Invert on a flat serving dish.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: rice pilaf 1
directions: Mix together rice, water, onion and garlic, Add oil to cover rice well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and cook on stove for a few minutes, then cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Flour both sides of pie crust, place in ungreased pie plate. Cook in 350° oven about 10 to 15 minutes, long enough so bottom of crust is slightly precooked.
This avoids a soggy crust.
Crumble bacon or sausage into small pieces.
Beat eggs, cream and salt. Stir in cheese and bacon/sausage.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake 20 minutes in 450° oven.
Turn oven down to 350°, bake 30 more minutes.
Quiche is cooked when knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: rolls
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder together. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix with 1 cup buttermilk.
Add to the flour mixture.
Add shortening and remainder of milk.
Mix all ingredients together, roll and cut.
Dip in melted butter (or margarine) and fold together.
Place in pan and bake at 450° for 12 minutes (may be baked at once or let stand).
Once prepared, can be covered with foil and frozen.

title: crushed doritos and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Add all ingredients except Doritos and shredded cheese. Cook until mixture bubbles. Crush Doritos in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. Pour mixture over Doritos. Add cheese on top. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well; fold in apples and pecans last.
Dough will be stiff.
Pour batter into 3 cake pans and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
You can also have a tube pan but you will need to increase your baking time by 10 minutes, testing with a toothpick to check to see if it's done.

title: apricot orange mold
directions: Measure juice and add water to make 2 cups.
Boil juice and pour over Jell-O.
Cool in refrigerator until thickened.
Beat the cream cheese into gelatin.
Whip the cream and fold into gelatin. Arrange oranges in mold and pour gelatin mixture over them or just mix oranges in.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: helen's vegetable hash
directions: Saute in a large frying pan until onions are clear.
Add seasonings to taste.
(I use Old Bay.)
When liquid has formed from juice of tomatoes, add to mixture one package of Lipton noodle sauce (I use sour cream and chives).
Simmer 7 minutes, stirring gently.
For more color, add a small jar of pimientos.

title: jane's baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, vanilla and sugar together.
Beat and add eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture alternately with milk.
Grease pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order listed.

title: mints
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar and cheese.
(Dough will be stiff.) Add flavor to taste and coloring to desired shade.
Break off small amount and roll into ball.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Press into flower or leave molds and let set at least 30 minutes.
Tap out of mold onto cookie sheet covered lightly with granulated sugar.

title: cottage pie
directions: Fry onion and first 2 tablespoons of butter.
Stir in flour. Add stock gradually until mixture thickens.
Season.
Add meat. Place mixture in well-greased pie dish.
Boil potatoes.
Mash with remaining margarine and milk.
Spread over meat mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: old fashion gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add molasses; mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with water.

title: pinwheel onion rolls
directions: Cook onions in butter until golden; cool.
Add salt and cayenne.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; mix only enough to dampen dry ingredients.
Roll into 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spread with onions.
Roll up as for jelly roll. Cut into eight 1-inch slices.
Put flat side down in greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix egg and evaporated milk.
Pour over rolls. Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: fruit and party punch
directions: Add water to orange juice and lemonade according to directions; mix with other liquids and place in ice.
Serves 50.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with margarine.
Line the pan with a layer of whole graham crackers.
Spread half the filling over the crackers.
Cover with another layer of whole graham crackers.
Spread the rest of the filling over the grahams and top with another layer of whole graham crackers.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, mix the margarine and crumbs. Press in pan.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly brown. Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until very tender.
Remove bones and skin.
Salt to taste.
Mix the mayonnaise, honey, curry powder and celery salt together well.
Add the cubed chicken and grapes.
Stir and chill. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter and add pepper and flour.
Add milk; mix well.
Simmer until creamy.
Remove from burner.
Blanch potatoes and carrots.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Sift the flour and sugar together and set aside.
In saucepan, mix the margarine, water and cocoa together.
Bring to rapid boil and pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well.
To this add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: no crust cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese and Ricotta cheese.
Add sugar and lightly beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in lemon juice, butter (melt in pan), vanilla extract, flour and cornstarch.
Blend well. Last, add sour cream.
Beat all ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter sides and bottom of spring-form pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until top is golden brown. Let sit in turned off oven for 2 hours.
Remove and cool for 1 hour.
Refrigerate.
Serve plain or topped with cherry or blueberry filling.

title: apple torte(sugar-free)
directions: Crust:
Blend the flour, 2 tablespoons fructose, oleo and salt.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: smoked meat loaf
directions: Place meat in bowl.
Mix eggs and brown sugar until well blended.
Mix rest of ingredients together with crackers and eggs. Place in foil-lined pan.
Flatten meat on top to 2-inch thickness.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until meat is done.
Place tomato sauce on meat, then bake.

title: best coconut pie
directions: Sprinkle coconut into bottom of pie crust; spread coconut evenly.
Mix other ingredients and pour over coconut.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: soup bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells evenly. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and Crisco together.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix flour and eggs.
Layer 1/2 the broccoli and 1/2 the cheeses in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Sprinkle canned onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudgy brownie
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup vegetable oil.
Add boiling water and stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup vegetable oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend completely. Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 19-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix. Serve in lettuce cups or in pretty bowl with party crackers or Ritz crackers on side.

title: homemade chili
directions: Mix hamburger, onions and salt (if desired).
Brown in pan. Add chili powder while browning (enough to taste).
Put in tomato juice; stir.
Add beans and stir.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours on low.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 inches oil to 375°.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot oil, frying a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, sifted with soda.
Add apples.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
(Nuts may be added.)

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Blend ingredients.
Put in pan and bake.

title: lunchbox bars
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add eggs and mix well. Add vanilla. In separate bowl, mix flour. salt and soda. Then mix into creamed mixture. Add last 3 ingredients. Bake at 350 degrees in greased 9 x 13 inch pan for approximately 20 - 25 minutes.

title: apriscotties
directions: In mixing bowl combine oatmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and almond extract.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is about the texture of coarse cornmeal.
Press slightly more than half the mixture into a greased 8 or 9 inch square baking pan.
Cover mixture with jam and then with remaining mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on rack.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Chop celery, carrots, onion and green pepper very fine.
Chop potatoes small.
Melt butter and saute all vegetables until they are tender. Stir in flour, then add chicken stock and milk.
Cook slowly until mixture thickens. Add American cheese and stir until all melted. When serving, add Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry the ground beef and small amount of oil until brown. Saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil.
Combine the meat and vegetables; simmer for 15 minutes.
Season with salt.
Place chili powder and ground cumin in top of double boiler.
Melt cheese; add can of tomatoes to spices and chili pepper.
You may only add 1/2 can, if desired.
Cut lettuce coarsely; cut tomatoes in chunks. Mix together.
Add Fritos; mix all ingredients, except melted cheese mixture.
Top with hot cheese; mix again.
Serve immediately.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup coconut for icing.
Combine remaining coconut, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together; add to coconut mixture alternately with buttermilk and flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Pour icing over cake; let stand for 2 hours before removing from pan.

title: mud
directions: Mix together and press in an 8X8 pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cube chicken in small cubes and saut in butter.
Bring asparagus and 1/2 teaspoon salt to full boil; drain.
Put asparagus in long pan; cover with chicken.
Bring soup, mushrooms, milk and Worcestershire sauce just to the boiling point.
DO NOT BOIL.
Pour over chicken, place cut cheese slices over soup mixture and sprinkle cubed toast over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Combine ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on high for 3 to 4 hours, or on low for 6 hours.

title: blueberry cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour mixture into crust. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Spread blueberry filling on top and chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and rinse with cold water.
Add vegetables and seasoning and pour in dressing.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: coconut bars
directions: Spread this over baked crust.
Bake for 25- 30 minutes at 350 degrees or till toothpick comes out clean.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Rub out all lumps, then add shortening.
Rub into dry ingredients until it disappears.
Beat eggs into a small bowl and add buttermilk, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until well combined.
Chill one hour or overnight.
Dust hands with flour and roll into balls the size of ping pong balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Grease bottom of a drinking glass first, then dip into sugar for each cookie.
Press about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: ham souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Press one can crescent rolls into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: catalina mexican salad
directions: Cook potatoes and break eggs into same boiling water to cook (at the same time).
Dice pickles and onions.
Add pickle juice, mustard, mayonnaise and
butter to taste.
Mix in mixer and serve warm.

title: sugar-free cookies(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix flour with baking powder.
Cream egg, butter and gelatin, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture, blending well.
Roll out cookie dough; cut into shapes or put through a cookie press.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 minutes, or until edges are brown.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in hot milk.
Pour over dry bread crumbs.
Add squash, cheese, eggs and onion.
Pour into baking dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° until firm.

title: sunday pecan coffee cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream together the sugar, oil and zest.
Add the egg and egg whites; mix completely. Blend in the Low-Fat Blend.
Add the vanilla and lemon juice; combine.
Slowly add the flour and baking powder, stirring until completely blended.
Lightly spray or wipe a 10-inch Bundt pan with vegetable oil, then lightly dust with flour.
Pour 2/3 of the batter into the pan.
In a small bowl, combine the pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle the nut mixture evenly over the batter, then gently pour in the remaining batter.
Place in the oven; bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the cake comes out clean.
Yields 24 slices.

title: greenbrier famed pumpkin muffins *
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin and margarine.
Blend in eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon into well-greased miniature muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over muffins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: hattie shannon's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and peanut butter; add beaten eggs. Sift flour; measure and sift again with salt and soda.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and nuts to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Mold into balls; place on cookie sheet and flatten with fork, scoring both ways.
Bake in moderate oven, 350° to 375°, for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in two greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool thoroughly before freezing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pumpkin-cheese cake pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; spread on unbaked pie shell.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and let cool.
Crumble 1 of the layers of cake in bowl (large bowl or punch bowl).
Use pineapple juice over crumbled cake.
Mix 1 box pudding and pour over cake.
Add enough Cool Whip to cover pudding.
Put small amount of pie filling around rim of bowl on top of Cool Whip.
Put pineapple in center; spread over remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Repeat with other layer of cake, pudding, pie filling, Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts (save more of pie filling, Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts to go on top).

title: tuna mushroom casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water and bouillon to a boil, stirring to dissolve.
Add the next eight ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: noncarbonated punch
directions: Add water to orange juice and lemonade according to directions on cans.
Mix with pineapple juice and cranberry juice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat in deep dish pie crust.
Top with crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cool.
Saute onion in stick of butter. Combine all the ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into large casserole dish.
Crush a stack of Ritz crackers into crumbs; sprinkle on top.
Melt 1 stick of butter; drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked squash surprise
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain, mash and season.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except stuffing and Flav-O-Rich butter. Mix Flav-O-Rich butter and stuffing; divide.
Line casserole with stuffing (little more than half of it).
Add squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Blend milk, coconut, cream cheese and sugar for 5 minutes. Add the Cool Whip and pour into the pie crust.
Sprinkle with coconut and freeze for 4 hours.

title: date bars
directions: Cook dates, sugar and water until thick (low temperature).
Add baking soda to melted butter.
Mix melted butter into mixture of brown sugar, flour and oatmeal.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat pan to 325°.
Put 1/2 crumb mixture on bottom of pan; press down. Add date mixture.
Crumble rest of crumb mixture on top.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tyropitakia (cheese triangles)
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Combine cheeses with eggs and blend well.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes.
Cut filo into 3 x 5-inch strips.
Taking 1 piece at a time, brush with melted butter. Place 1 rounded teaspoonful of cheese mixture at lower left hand corner and fold up to form triangle.
Continue folding to end of strip.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with additional melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crisp and golden brown.
Yields 60 to 70 triangles.

title: pear pie and topping
directions: Pour mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Bake approximately 15 minutes at 350°.
Add topping.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
"Dump" in the can of pie filling.
Next "dump" in can of pineapple.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the top.
Cut the butter in small pieces over the top of the cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheesy hamburger
directions: Cook hamburger until done; drain.
Let set.
Fix 2 boxes of macaroni and cheese by the directions on box.
Mix together and you are done.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan at 350° for 60 minutes or until tests done.

title: eight minute light-n-fruity pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend in Cool Whip, then whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill if necessary until mixture is set.
Spoon into crust.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans or parsley.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll in pecans or parsley.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine condensed milk, pudding mix and water.
Beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into individual serving dishes.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add vinegar, vanilla and oil.
Mix and then add the water.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan which has been greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
If making cupcakes, bake for 15 minutes.

title: beef and broccoli with mushrooms
directions: Cook beef cubes in 1 tablespoon oil.
Drain.
Add packages of gravy mix and water.
Stir.
Add cut up broccoli and mushrooms. Simmer until broccoli is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: cereal balls
directions: Melt first three ingredients in double boiler or microwave. Dip large marshmallows in mixture, then roll in Rice Krispies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir together with remainder of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in an 8 x 8-inch pan with lid.
The first 1/2 hour cook with lid on.
The last half hour cook with lid off.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab dip delight
directions: Combine all ingredients except crab in double boiler.
Heat until smooth.
Add crab meat, mix and chill.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Top with chips and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Cream sugar and oil until dissolved, then add balance of ingredients.
Mix well.
Keeps in refrigerator until needed.
It is better if you let set 24 hours before using.
Marinate cabbage overnight in self-seal bag, turning frequently for best flavor. Makes 1 quart.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Stir in sugar and flour. Add Pet milk and sweet milk.
Cook in double boiler until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Stir into custard and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Chill before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Blend all together.
Reserve 1/2 of beef to roll cheese ball in.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: limpa bread
directions: Mix flour in separate bowls.
Mix yeast in warm water, then add other ingredients (only 1 teaspoon each of seed, put rest on top of bread.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Mix egg with 1 tablespoon of milk and brush on bread.

title: dill pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in cold water overnight.
Pack in sterilized jars cold.
To each quart, add alum, dill seed and pepper.
Mix vinegar, salt and water; heat until boiling.
Pour over each jar. Be sure they seal.
Put in hot water bath for a few minutes.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix refried beans and taco mix.

title: brownies
directions: In microwave, melt margarine and chocolate.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.
These brownies are fudgelike in consistency.

title: diet pineapple cheesecake
directions: Place drained pineapple in blender with half of its juice. Add gelatin and hot water; blend 2 minutes.
Add dry milk and remainder of juice, sugar substitute, vanilla, butter flavoring and lemon juice.
Blend for 3 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch pan, sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and allow to set 1 hour before serving.

title: drop rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt butter; let cool.
Add egg (beaten well); add sugar.
Add butter mixture to water and yeast mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours before using.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake at 425° until browned.

title: bok choy
directions: Rinse bok choy in cold water.
Cut stalks diagonally in 1-inch pieces and leaves into thin shreds.
In a large nonstick skillet, heat oil and the stems first and saute, tossing about 2 minutes. Add garlic, leaves, fructose, soy sauce and sesame oil. Continue cooking over high heat 2 minutes more.
Contains 40 calories, 0 cholesterol, 5 g carbohydrates, 1 g protein, 59 mg sodium and 2 gr fat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Arrange in a buttered baking dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Spoon over broccoli.
Top with pimentos, crackers, nuts and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; mix well and then add cold water.
Let jello thicken, but not jell, then mix rest of ingredients and add to jello.
Mix good and then chill.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix well and bake in 2 (9-inch) pie shells for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rocky road squares
directions: In top of double boiler over boiling water, melt chocolate chips with Eagle Brand milk and margarine.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in wax paper lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Remove from pan, peel off wax paper and cut into squares. Makes about 40 squares.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Wash and drain berries.
Lay berries out to dry.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Clean chicken breasts. Melt butter and add Italian seasoning. Brush on chicken. Sprinkle chicken with seasoning salt as needed. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: baked pork chops and macaroni
directions: Par boil pork chops and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook macaroni and add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Put in layers in pan.
Put slices of cheese on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: white bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and butter and cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture; add 3 cups flour.
beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Remove from oven and arrange pecans over baked dough.
Mix together eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla; pour over entire surface.
Return to oven for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove, cool and cut into bars.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is cold, cover with mixture of pudding, milk and cream cheese. Spread Cool Whip over this layer.
Sprinkle pineapple, coconut and nuts over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until served.

title: daiquiri pie
directions: Combine
pudding
mix,
gelatin
and sugar in saucepan. Stir in
cup
of
water
and
the
eggs; blend well.
Add remaining water
and cook; stir over medium heat until mixture comes to
a full boil.
Remove from heat; stir in rum.
Chill. Thoroughly
blend
Cool Whip into chilled mixture.
Spoon into pie crust and chill until firm, about two hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip and lime slices if desired.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat margarine and 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add oats and flour.
Mix well. Spread evenly onto bottom of pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar at medium speed until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over partially cooled crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until middle appears set.
Chill.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Steam spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Bake in 2 1/2-quart baking dish on 350° for 35 minutes or use scoop and bake individual servings on cookie sheet.

title: flo's squash souffle
directions: Mash squash.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart ring mold.
Set in pan of hot water and bake until firm in 350° oven.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions and fill paper baking cups 2/3 full.
Beat cream cheese with sugar until well blended, then beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful cheese mixture into each cupcake and bake 20 to 25 minutes until done.

title: pizza twists
directions: Soften yeast from hot roll mix according to package directions.
Stir in 1 egg.
Combine flour mixture from the hot roll mix, the pepperoni, cheeses, onion, oregano and garlic powder.
Stir into yeast mixture; mix well.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down; turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Cut into 24 portions; roll each to a rope 10 inches long.
Fold rope in half; twist 2 or 3 times.
Seal ends with a little water.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until almost double, 30 to 45 minutes.
Combine egg yolk and water; brush on rolls.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove rolls to wire racks to cool.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: strawberry yogurt smoothy
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and enjoy. Also great with fresh peaches and peach yogurt.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Place ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool cake and frost with the following.

title: mushrooms berkley
directions: Cut up everything.
Saute onion and butter until transparent. Mix brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce until smooth paste.
Add wine and stir.
When onions are clear, add mushrooms and pepper.
Then add wine sauce.
Simmer over medium flame for 45 minutes.

title: oriental rice
directions: Combine scallops, shrimp and crabmeat.
Cut up onions in a frying pan and saute in butter or margarine.
Add scallops, shrimp and crabmeat.
Be careful not to overcook.
When done, add to boiled rice.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
If desired, soy sauce can be added.

title: pecan bourbon pie(an old kentucky recipe)
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Line pie pan with plain pastry.
(I bake crust 10 minutes at 450° before adding filling.)
Pour filling into crust and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325° or until filling just sets.
Do not overbake. Chill and serve.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat until red hots melt.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix dirt, swamp water, crushed bones and fat.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Add grass, muddy water, squashed bugs and worms.
Stir until bugs dissolve.
Drop onto wax paper; let cool.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; set aside.
Add melted butter and eggs to the milk; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; stir just enough to get an even mixture.
If too thick, add more milk until mixture pours easily.
Pour to desired size on hot greased griddle.
Brown both sides.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast on both sides in skillet (without oil), then place in crock-pot.
Take chopped onion, chopped green pepper, fresh ginger and minced garlic; stir-fry in oil in skillet until tender. Add soy sauce and beef broth; bring to a boil and pour over roast.
Add whole potatoes, onions and carrots.
Cook for 4 to 5 hours, or until meat is tender.
Baste vegetables every hour.

title: brownies
directions: Bake in jelly roll pan for 28 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: friendship or russian tea
directions: Mix all together well in a large airtight canister.
Shake well before each use.
Use one teaspoon more or less to taste, per cup of hot water.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Serve immediately.

title: german chocolate turtle bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler. Mix cake mix, margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chips over this crust; pour the caramel mix on and dab the remaining cake mixture on top.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Mash with margarine and set aside. Fry hamburger and onions until crumbly.
Drain.
Add gravy mix with water and add to hamburger.
Layer hamburger mixture, mashed potatoes and then cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add Cheez Whiz to melt.
Stir in rice and soup; cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Add to cheese mixture.
Put into oven-proof dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Heat through until cheese is melted.

title: cheezy chicken
directions: Combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Put dough in 8 triangles.
Put 3 tablespoons of chicken on wide end of triangle and roll.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk and 1/4 cup cheese. Heat until cheese melts.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture in 10 x 10-inch pan.
Add rolls.
Pour remaining soup on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and spread on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on cool dough.
Top with veggies (carrots, peppers, tomatoes, broccoli).
Chill overnight and cut into bars.

title: fresh green beans with sour cream sauce
directions: Cook beans for 10 to 12 minutes in salted water.
Remove 1 cup water when cooked.
Heat butter in saucepan.
Add onion; cook 3 minutes.
Add vinegar and sugar; cook 1 minute.
Add reserved liquid.
Season with salt and pepper; cook 7 minutes.
Remove pan from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Add beans; mix gently and let simmer 3 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix refried beans and picante sauce (use according to taste). Sprinkle cheese over top. Add chopped tomatoes to top it off. You're ready to start dipping!!

title: egg and sausage pies
directions: Cook sausage; drain grease.
Mix sausage, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into two pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: lakeway chicken salad
directions: Artichokes, rice and chicken combine to make a great luncheon salad.
Serves 8.

title: grandma shelby's chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add water and cook over low fire.
Stir until thick.
Add vanilla. Pour into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
This recipe was given to me by my mother-in-law as a young bride and I wrote it on a brown paper bag.
I still use it.
Thanks to Mamie Lou Shelby.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar and syrup in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, peanuts and corn flakes.
Stir until blended.
Press into a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Put pan into a 200° oven just long enough to melt chips.
Spread chocolate; cool.
Cut into bars.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
In a saucepan, cook spinach and cheese in margarine until cheese melts.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
For thicker quiche, use 20 ounces frozen spinach and 3 eggs.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Clean and remove seeds.
Put peppers in blender with 1 cup of the vinegar and mix until fine.
Put pepper mixture into pan with 6 1/2 cups sugar. Add remaining vinegar.
Cook until boiling and slow boil for 10 minutes. Wipe off skim using wooden spoon.
Add the Certo and stir.
Add red or green food coloring.
Boil 1 minute.
Put in jars and seal.

title: beef junk
directions: Cut steaks into 2 to 3-inch strips.
Brown in covered skillet until done.
Add onion, chopped.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add all gravy mix as directed on package.
Let simmer about 10 minutes. Mix flour and water until paste is made and add to mix to thicken gravy.
Simmer to desired consistency.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken curry
directions: Melt honey and butter first.
Then add the rest of ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Baste consistently.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pea pods with beef
directions: Slice steak against grain into 1/4 x 3-inch strips.
Mix with soy sauce.
In skillet over high heat, cook garlic in oil.
Add steak and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle salt over pan; add pea pods and celery; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup water, pepper and sugar.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add steak; sprinkle with wine and stir-fry 30 seconds.
Blend cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water; add to skillet.
Cook 1 minute or until sauce thickens.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Into a large bowl, place soup, Colby cheese, onion, margarine, pepper and salt.
Mix together until thoroughly blended.
Put potatoes into 13 1/2 x 10 1/4-inch pan.
Pour the soup and cheese mixture over the shredded potatoes.
Mix thoroughly into the potatoes; use either a kitchen spoon or gloved hands.
Place in oven, uncovered, for 30 minutes, or until the casserole is lightly browned on top.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: In a large bowl, combine strawberries and sugar; mix well. Let stand 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine pectin and lemon juice; pour over strawberries.
Stir thoroughly for 3 minutes (a few sugar crystals will remain).
Spoon into glass or plastic containers; cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours. Store in freezer.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: fayette county beef stew
directions: Brown meat over medium heat until lightly browned.
Add 1/2 c. water to pan; stir to loosen any drippings.
Place meat in a large roasting pan and mix in all remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 3 1/2 hrs.
Makes 6 servings - 580 calories each serving.

title: belle's crab dip
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese and heat.
Add crab meat and garlic to taste.
Serve hot or cold.
It's disappears either way.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots until tender-crisp.
Remove from hot water and chill.
Alternate layers of carrots, onions and green pepper rings.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat to a boil. Pour mixture over vegetables.
Keep in refrigerator, covered.
Can be kept crisp for several weeks.

title: green pea lettuce salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, peas, Miracle Whip, bacon bits and cheese.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: mother's homemade ice cream
directions: Make custard of milk, cornstarch, egg yolks and sugar, preferably in double boiler.
Chill overnight.
When ready to freeze, add beaten egg whites, vanilla and cream.
Freeze in hand cranked freezer or an electric one.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix altogether and put into 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Add enough whole milk to bring mixture to fill line.
Freeze.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage for 20 minutes.
Boil cabbage slightly.
Cook rice slightly.
Mix beef, onions, rice, salt and pepper.
Wrap all ingredients into cabbage leaves.
Put in cooker and cover with tomato juice.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Put into skillet with grease that you have fried bacon in. Remove bacon for later use.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer approximately 20 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top and serve.

title: creamy coffee punch
directions: Dissolve coffee and sugar in water; stir in vanilla.
Stir cream into well beaten eggs.
Add coffee mixture.
Beat in ice cream.
Chill at least one hour.
Just before serving, beat to blend.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts or 20 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle first with raisins and the 2/3 cup of coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Garnish with remaining coconut.

title: holiday snowflakes
directions: *You may substitute almond bark.

title: meat loaf with sauce
directions: Combine and
soak
crumbs
and tomato juice.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Grease large loaf pan and fill with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with tasty sauce.

title: beef stew and dumplings
directions: Cut meat into cubes and brown in the hot fat.

Add water, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, sliced onion and seasonings. Cover and simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Add carrots, onions and potatoes the last 30 minutes. Remove meat and vegetables and thicken the gravy as follows:

title: blueberry buckle and filling
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Fold in blueberries.
Place in a greased 10 x 15-inch pan (I use a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake it 5 minutes longer).

title: strawberry charlotte russe
directions: Cut jelly roll into 1/2-inch slices and place around the bottom and sides of an oiled 2 1/2-quart mixing bowl.
In another container, dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add marshmallows and partially defrosted strawberries, stirring until marshmallows dissolve.
Add lemon juice.
Chill until partially congealed; beat until fluffy.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Blend in whipped cream and nuts.
Pile mixture lightly into jelly roll-lined bowl.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and serve.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix.
Use as dip with any fruit.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in 9 x 10-inch or 10 x 12-inch glass dish.
Spread mayonnaise mixture over top of all as if icing a cake.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: e-z cabbage rolls
directions: Immerse cabbage in large kettle of boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes or until leaves are limp; separate leaves.
Mix meat, onion and rice; add salt and pepper to season.
Add 1 can tomato soup; mix well.
Place about 1/4 cup of meat mixture on each cabbage leaf; fold sides of leaf to center and roll leaf around mixture.
Place lapped end down in baking dish.
Cover with the other can of soup.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
Spoon into hot fish grease.

title: filet mercedes
directions: Melt a generous amount of butter and rub into meat portion. Sprinkle with a light amount of pepper and paprika and rub in. Wrap slice of bacon around the side of the filet.
Hold in place with a toothpick.
Place under broiler or on the grill to desired temperature.
While cooking put mushrooms in pan and saute in butter or oil.
Add up to 1/4 cup cooking wine.
Add small amount of orange juice and boil.
Add cornstarch to thicken to desired consistency.
Add sauce over cooked filet and serve.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° until brown on top, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy mocha frozen dessert
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve coffee granules in hot water.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine cookie crumbs, 1/2 cup of pecans and butter.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Blend in coffee mixture, milk and chocolate syrup.
Fold in whipped topping and spread over crust.
Sprinkle remaining pecans on top.
Freeze. Definitely not low calorie, but delicious!

title: galumpki-bobchi's recipe
directions: Kill the cabbage.
That is, cut out the core; put it in a large pot.
Cover with water and boil it just until the leaves are tender enough to peel off, about 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook the rice with the water until absorbed.
Mix egg and spice in a big bowl. Add the meat and rice and mix it all together.
Take a fistful or a big spoonful of the rice mixture.
Put one on each cabbage leaf and fold the leaves over.
Place them, folded side down, in a deep baking pan.
Mix puree with some spices and pour it over.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 30 minutes, then cover and bake 30 minutes more.
If you wish, you can use green peppers instead of cabbage.
Stuff the peppers with the meat mix and cook the same.

title: date pudding
directions: Make a syrup of the first 3 ingredients, boiling until well melted.
Make it in the same pan you will bake pudding in, either square or oblong.
In a bowl, combine brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, milk, dates and nuts.
Stir well to mix.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt and add to batter, mixing well. Carefully pour batter into pan of syrup but do not stir.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes according to oven, suggest 350°.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: margaret's home style barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for chicken.
Put chicken in baking pan and pour mixture over it.
Cook 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: If desired, top with crumbled eggs and bacon.

title: stir-fry lemon chicken
directions: Cut chicken in cubes.
Mix lemon rind, soy sauce, sherry and 2 teaspoons cornstarch together.
Marinate the chicken.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add rice, onion and garlic stirring until rice is hot.
Add 2 cups broth, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 25 minutes.
Cut peppers into strips.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in pan. Stir in peppers.
Mix 1/2 teaspoon cornstarch with remaining broth and set aside.
Heat last 2 tablespoons oil and stir-fry chicken. Add broth and cornstarch to pan.
Mix until thickened.
Mix rice, peppers and top with chicken.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Stew chicken with salt, pepper and bay leaf.
After cooking, debone chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces.
In a large saucepan, saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender. Stir in soups and Ro-Tel.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, layer tortillas, chicken, soup and cheese.
Repeat layers 3 times, ending with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly and cheese is lightly browned.
Can be frozen before or after cooking.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: the perfect blueberry muffin
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Line twelve 3-inch or fourteen 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups with paper liners. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Beat butter and 1 cup sugar in a large mixer bowl at medium speed until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk and vanilla. Beginning and ending with dry ingredients, until batter is smooth. Crush 1/2 cup berries and add to batter. Fold remaining berries into batter with rubber spatula. Divide and spoon batter into muffin pan cups. Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon sugar. Bake for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool muffins in pan 5 minutes before removing. Place on wire rack. Makes 12 muffins.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Use the directions on frozen orange juice and lemonade.
Add whiskey.
Freeze.
Serve each glass with 1/3 of the slush mixture and add 7-Up.

title: tony's awesome chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare and bake brownies according to package directions. Cool and crumble. Reserve 1/2 crumbs for top. Make instant pudding according to package directions. In bottom of 4 qt trifle dish or straight sided glass dish, layer 1/2 of crumbled cake. Sprinkle with 1/2 of the brewed coffee. Next, layer 1/2 puddings, 1/2 whipped topping, and 1/2 of the cookies. Repeat layers, adding reserved crumbled cake on top of last layer of cookies. Refrigerate 24 hrs. Keep leftovers in refrigerator. Makes 16 to 18 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown the ground beef, onion and bell pepper. Add the tomato sauce, corn and tamales.
Mix well on low heat. Add garlic, chili powder and salt to taste.
Add half of the cheese and olives to the mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Sprinkle with the rest of the cheese and olives. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: streusel
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring well.
Fold in raisins or chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: ham and cheese omelet
directions: Melt butter in nonstick pan.
Mix other ingredients together; cut ham in little pieces.
Cook on one side until halfway done, then flip over and finish cooking.
Fold in half and serve.

title: connie's pear relish
directions: Grind all together.
Cook 45 minutes.
Put in hot jars to seal.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook together sugar, syrup and butter until sugar is dissolved.
Boil rapidly until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Pour over popped corn in large mixing bowl.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put about 1/4 cup oil in iron skillet and
place in preheated 425° oven. Let skillet and oil get very
hot.	Remove from oven and add mixture. Bake at 425° for about
to
minutes	or until done. Top with grated cheese.

title: corn pudding
directions: Pour corn into bowl.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Beat well.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Grease baking dish and pour mixture in. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sudden salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: blackpot shrimp get together
directions: Dice the peppers to about 1/4 the size of the shrimp.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil until drop of water dances on top.
Stir-fry peppers and onions for 1 minute; set aside.
In same pot, heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil until hot and saute ginger and garlic until slightly brown and aromatic.
Add shrimp, sugar and black pepper.
Stir-fry approximately 5 minutes until each shrimp has assumed a pinkish/red color.
Add soy sauce and vinegar.
Heat to steaming.
Boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Cover.
Allow shrimp to steam in covered pot for approximately 5 minutes.
(Oversteaming causes shells to separate from shrimp.)
Mix in peppers and onions. Garnish and serve in pot.
Serve with rice or French bread.

title: peanut crinkles
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; add egg.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon and press with fork.
Bake in moderate oven 12 minutes. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: kurt's chocolate cookies
directions: Soften butter.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes on a greased baking sheet.
Cookies should come out and stay moist.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine in microwave. Mix peanut butter in margarine. Add powdered sugar. Roll into balls. Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in pan. Use toothpick to dip balls into mixture. Place on wax paper.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; stir until smooth.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and pat out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 16 biscuits.

title: ziti and panchetta with cheese
directions: Boil ziti al dente.
Dice the Panchetta and fry in large pan. Remove when browned.
Add ziti and the grated cheeses to bacon drippings over low heat and stir.
Beat eggs and stir in.
Don't overcook eggs.
Just add pepper to taste and serve.

title: german style green beans
directions: Drain 1/3 cup stock from beans.
Heat beans in remaining liquid.
Fry bacon until crisp and remove from pan.
Blend flour into drippings.
Add bean stock, sour cream, salt and vinegar. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Drain beans of remaining liquid.
Arrange in a serving dish.
Top with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: fruit upside-down cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter and fruit in bottom of sheet cake pan. Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour batter on top and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let cool 30 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sausage soup
directions: Remove skin from sausage.
Crumble and saute in a large pot until browned.
Drain.
Add onions and green peppers.
Saute until tender.
Add broth and wine, bring to a boil and add tomato sauce, puree, garlic powder, oregano, basil, parsley.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook uncovered for 1 hour.
Pasta may be added the last 15 minutes.
If a thinner soup is desired, pre-cook pasta and add just before serving.
Serve with grated cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in the center of pie filling comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: oats 'n wheat blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine rolled oats and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper baking cups. Stir honey, oil and egg into rolled oats mixture.
Mix well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In a small bowl, combine whole wheat flour, baking soda and salt. Blend well. Add to rolled oats mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries. Fill greased muffin cups about 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine water, sugar and cherries.
Bring to a boil gently for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Add pineapple (do not drain).
Add nuts and Coke. Stir.
Place in mold or dish and chill.
Great for the holidays.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Line 9 x 5 inch loaf pan with buttered waxed paper; set aside. Combine corn syrup, 1/4 c. water and sugar in heavy, small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil. Wash down side of pan frequently with pastry brush dipped in hot water to remove sugar crystals. Carefully clip candy thermometer to side of pan (do not let bulb touch bottom of pan). Continue to cook until mixture reaches the hard ball stage (255°). Meanwhile, beat egg white and cream of tartar with heavy duty electric mixer until stiff but not dry. Slowly pour hot syrup into egg white mixture, beating constantly. Add vanilla; beat until candy forms soft peaks and starts to lose its gloss. Spoon mixture into prepared pan. Cut into 3 strips lengthwise, then crosswise in center. Freeze until firm.

Line baking sheet with waxed paper; set aside. Melt caramels with 3 Tbsp. water in heavy, small saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally. Arrange pecans on waxed paper. Working quickly, drop 1 piece of frozen candy mixture into melted caramels to coat completely. Place on prepared baking sheet to set. Repeat with remaining candy pieces, reheating caramels if mixture becomes too thick. Cut logs into 1/2 inch slices. Store in refrigerator in airtight container between layers of waxed paper or freeze up to 3 months. Makes 6 (5 inch) rolls.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine in order.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch pan (or bowl) and sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Chill until firm.
Serve as salad or dessert.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand and make into walnut size balls. Melt 2 semi-sweet chocolate (8 ounces) bars in double boiler.
(Do not let water boil hard under chocolate.)
Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper.
Put in freezer for 10 minutes (on tray) before putting in container.
Store in refrigerator.

title: crunchy tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soup, noodles and sour cream. Add mushrooms, tuna, thyme, salt and pepper.
Pour into an oiled 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: one-bowl macaroon cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon 1 inch apart onto well-greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Recipe may be doubled.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: frank bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix ingredients and top with franks. Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and flavoring and beat well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto pie pan sprinkled with granulated sugar.
Place on greased sheet pan sugar side up.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: jelly roll yellow sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a jelly roll pan with 1 tablespoon shortening.
Sprinkle well with cake flour, shaking off loose flour.
Separate eggs; beat yolks 1 minute.
Add pinch of salt to egg whites and beat until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and continue beating whites until they cling to bottom and sides of bowl, then beat 1 minute longer.
Fold beaten egg yolks into egg whites gently but quickly.
Fold in sugar, flour and vanilla.
Do not overmix.

title: honey glaze for ham
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on ham about 45 minutes before ham is done cooking.

title: poached salmon with horseradish sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large skillet. Bring to a boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Add salmon. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Remove skillet from heat and let stand 8 minutes. Place salmon on platter.
Serve with accompanying Horseradish Sauce.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix
all
ingredients in a large saucepan and cool over low heat for 20 minutes.
This makes a sweet sauce.
Very good on ribs.

title: thick and sweet barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in a skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes, stirring often.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
May stir up and refrigerate the night before.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Line a jelly roll pan (or large cookie sheet with sides) with foil, then grease foil.
Line foil with graham crackers. Boil butter and sugar until sugar dissolves. Add pecans and pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool and break apart.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
In a plastic bag, mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, mix egg white and water.
Stir in pecans and mix until damp.
Pour pecans in bag to coat and shake well; spread on a baking sheet and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until dry.
Stir every 20 minutes during baking.
Do not freeze.
Keep in cool, dry place.
Makes 1 pound.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in 2-quart pot and cook until thickened. After mixture thickens, beat 2 eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup orange juice and 3 teaspoons vanilla.
Then add to rice mixture and blend.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Dressing:
Mix seasoning from soup with oil, vinegar and soy sauce.

title: beth's peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches.
Mix everything else together except butter. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cover rice with boiling water and set aside until water is absorbed.
Saute onion in oleo until golden brown.
Blend in rice, undiluted soup, cheese, broccoli and onion.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 can French fried onions. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes, or until onions are golden.
Serves 6 people.

title: hush puppies
directions: Put corn, tomatoes, peppers and onions in blender; blend until soupy.
Add eggs and sugar and put in large pan.
Add cornmeal and flour slowly.
Mix by hand until right consistency.
Best if left in refrigerator overnight.
