Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls in deep fat and fry until golden brown.
Serves 75 to 100 people.

title: low-fat fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt the margarine in saucepan over medium heat. Add garlic and saute 1 minute. Stir in flour. Gradually add milk, stirring with wire whisk until blended. Cook 8 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream cheese and cook 2 minutes. Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly, until it melts.
Pour over hot fettuccine. Top with remaining Parmesan cheese and parsley.
One cup contains 345 calories and 9.7 grams of fat.

title: cucumber, orange salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and chill for 8 minutes. Sprinkle with poppy seed pepper, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn and pea salad
directions: Pour water over peas to separate and drain.
Mix the corns together.
Add peas.
Heat vinegar and sugar until dissolved. Pour over vegetable mixture.
Marinate 24 hours or longer before serving.
Will keep 2 - 3 week in refrigerator.
Use slotted spoon to serve.
Serves 12 - 16.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Mix in bowl the dressing, preserves, water and onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken and cover with foil.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except the soup and form into balls like the size of golf balls but don't pack them too tight.
Roll in flour and brown well in a skillet.
Arrange meat balls in a casserole and pour over the soup diluted with 1 cup of water.
Dash of sherry if you are so inclined.
Cover and bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Grease bottom of deep dish (9-inch) pie plate.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, 1/3 cup sugar, nutmeg, butter, egg and milk.
Pour into pie plate.
Arrange peach slices over mixture, keeping 1/4-inch from edge.
Mix vanilla, cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved juice.
Spread over peaches, keeping from edge.
Combine cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until crust is browned.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together salt, flour, sugar and soda.
Add beaten eggs. Add the fruit cocktail and the juice.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the brown sugar and nuts on top of dough. Bake 1 hour in 300°
oven.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Roll into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Coat with chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: holiday macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions and drain. Combine milk, soup and cheese and simmer until cheese is melted. Mix macaroni, cheese sauce, onion, green and black pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish and bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or 6 to 8 minutes in microwave.

title: hamburger bean dish
directions: Cook hamburger and set aside.
Cook bacon and set aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients with bacon grease.
Add cooked hamburger and bacon.
Add all 4 types of beans and stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (or cook 6 to 8 hours in slow cooker).

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and mash.
Add butter, salt and celery salt; scald milk and add to potatoes.
Beat eggs well; stir into soup when boiling point is reached.
Serve immediately.
Serve with 1 tablespoon of whipped cream.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.
Place beef in pan.
Wrap bacon around chicken.
Lay on beef.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken, cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Cover for the first hour.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix shredded cabbage, 1/4 cup grated onion, Ramen noodles (scrunched), slivered almonds and sesame seeds.
Toast almonds in 350° oven until browned before adding.

title: kate's caramel corn
directions: Spread freshly popped corn in roasting pan.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, firm ball stage.
Add baking soda.
Pour over popcorn. Stir well and place in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Slice cucumbers and onions.
Add cooled liquid.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Pour into pint jars with tight fitting lids.
Store in refrigerator.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Mix gently with Rice Chex.
Cool 5 minutes.
Shake in sealed large mixing bowl with powdered sugar.

title: grape salad
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and vinegar until thick, then cool.
Fold together remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Stir in pumpkin, egg and vanilla. In another bowl, mix dry ingredients together.
Stir gradually into pumpkin mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
With teaspoon, drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf cordon blue
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.

Beat eggs in a large bowl. Add 2 tablespoons parsley, bread crumbs, broth, garlic, salt, tarragon, mustard and pepper. Beat well. Mix in ground beef. Set aside. Saute onions in butter until soft. Blend cheese, ham, remaining parsley and
onions in a medium bowl. Set aside.
Divide meat mixture into 2 equal parts.
Pat one part into loaf pan. Top with cheese mixture.
Pat remaining meat mixture on top of cheese. Bake for 45 minutes. Drain off fat.
Bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: baked ice cream
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
On cookie sheet, arrange cake slices in a single layer, leaving some space between each slice; spread each slice with 1 1/2 tsp jam.
Top each cake slice with a scoop of ice cream; freeze at least 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare meringue.

In clean, grease-free bowl, using electric mixer at medium speed, beat egg whites just until stiff peaks form. Continuing to beat, gradually add sugar; beat until glossy. Remove cookie sheet from freezer.

Immediately spread meringue over ice cream, working quickly to cover entire scoop and being sure meringue touches edges of cake slices on all sides to seal. Bake until meringue is lightly browned, about 5 minutes; serve immediately.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken to form marinade. Remove skin from chicken legs.
Place chicken in a baking dish, coat with marinade and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes basting occasionally.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix
all dry ingredients together.
Add liquids and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: overnight apple cinnamon french toast
directions: In a large skillet melt butter.
Add apple slices and cook stirring occasionally.
Add brown sugar, syrup and cinnamon. Cook, stirring
until sugar dissolves.
Pour apple mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange and fit bread slices over apples. Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes. Invert on serving plate.

title: bananas foster
directions: Combine the butter, sugar and cinnamon in a flambe pan or skillet.
Place the pan over low heat on top of stove.
Cook, stirring until the sugar dissolves.
Stir in the banana liqueur, then place the bananas in the pan.
When bananas begin to brown, add the rum.
Continue to cook sauce until rum is hot, tip the pan slightly to ignite the rum.
When flames subside, lift the bananas out of the pan and place 4 pieces over each portion of ice cream. Spoon warm sauce over top of ice cream.
Serve immediately.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake at 350° in ovenproof dish for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with Triscuits.
Makes 2 cups.

title: breakfast on the run(low-calorie)
directions: In a small bowl, combine apple butter and mustard.
Stir to mix well.
Spread 1 tablespoon mixture on each muffin half.
In another small bowl, combine ham, onion and cheese.
Stir to mix well.
Place one-sixth of mixture on each muffin half.
Broil until topping is bubbly.
Serves 6; 1/2 English muffin per serving.

title: park avenue squares
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Batter is stiff.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, brown beef; drain and set aside. In the same saucepan, saute onion, carrots, celery, basil and parsley in 1 tablespoon butter until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Add broth, potatoes and beef; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Beat eggs and soak chicken pieces in eggs for 8 hours or overnight.
Bread chicken pieces in crumbs.
Brown quickly in margarine that has been melted in skillet.
Place in large casserole.
Add the chicken broth and drained mushrooms that have been heated together.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy caramel breakfast rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls on greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding and brown sugar over rolls.
Drizzle butter and nuts over all.
Cover with Saran Wrap and place in cold oven.
Let rise overnight.
In the morning, remove Saran Wrap.
Turn oven on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy cauliflower
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 cup cheese and set aside.

title: dole golden layer cake
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, whipped topping (Cool Whip) and pudding mix.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut cake lengthwise in "thirds".
Drizzle with liqueur.
Spread on one-third pudding mixture over bottom layer of cake.
Top with second layer. Repeat, ending with pudding.
Chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with toasted, sliced almonds.
Serves around 12 people.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar, 1/2 cup kraut juice and vinegar.
Boil to a rolling boil.
Pour over vegetables and let set for at least 12 hours.

title: health bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dilute 1 yeast cake in 1/4 cup warm water and add to mixture.
Add flour.
Let rise and punch down.
Bake 400° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: Beat egg whites until they peak.
Bring sugar and water to a boil; place marshmallow pieces in beaten egg whites.
Beat until mixture is cool and thick.

title: splinter's easy pizzas
directions: Toast the English muffin.
Spread each half with tomato sauce. Top with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven until the cheese melts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
form into ball.
Mix 1 tablespoon chili powder
and
tablespoon paprika and sprinkle on outside of ball.
Wrap in wax paper and then in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: butter brickle cake
directions: Bake devil's food cake as directed.
Poke holes in cake.
Mix caramel ice cream topping and Pet milk.
Warm in a microwave. Poke holes in cake.
Top with thawed Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Heath Bits over top.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix everything together real good and if the salad is still a little dry, add more mayonnaise or Miracle Whip.
Let it set overnight for the best taste.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch rectangular pan.
Measure cereal into a large bowl.
Microwave the marshmallows, syrup, chocolate chips and margarine 2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until mixture is melted.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal.
Press in pan.
Let stand 1 hour or refrigerate for a firmer bar.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix everything.
Marinate 12 hours in refrigerator.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, pour oil, then cake mix, instant pudding mix, eggs, water and oil; stir with fork.
Add chocolate chips; mix in.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Delicious warm with ice cream.

title: roast pork tenderloin
directions: Cut a pocket lengthwise in meat. Stuff with garlic and fruit. If necessary tie together. Place in baking dish. Pour sherry over meat and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Pour milk over oats and let stand 5 minutes.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add beaten eggs to rolled oats mixture.
Add butter.
Add sifted ingredients.
Mix quickly and lightly.
If not used right away, store in refrigerator and mix again before using.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Saute bacon until almost crisp.
Add onion; continue to saute until onion is tender.
Drain excess fat.
Combine bacon and onion with beans and remaining ingredients in a 1-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine ingredients and mix until a very stiff dough forms. Chill the dough. Roll dough into balls. If desired, roll into sugar. Place 2-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Cook for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: sugar pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Bring to boil the water and margarine, then add hot mixture to the dry ingredients.
Add whipping cream and vanilla to mixture.
Pour into 2 separate pie crusts (unbaked).
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2.

title: brussels sprouts with water chestnuts
directions: Clean and trim sprouts.
Saute sprouts in butter until fork-tender.
Add sliced water chestnuts.
Heat thoroughly. Enjoy.

title: low calorie tuna chop suey
directions: Over low heat, cook celery and onion in 2 tablespoons water. Cover skillet to steam cook, keeping heat very low.
When soft and tender, remove from heat and add rice, water and seasonings. Bring to boil; turn heat to low.
Cover and cook slowly until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed (about 20 minutes).
Fold in tuna and remove from heat.
Cover and let stand several minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients, using hot water to rinse out molasses cup.
Mix in dry ingredients, using more flour if needed. Refrigerate dough.
Roll out and cut with a cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in small amount of water.
combine rest of ingredients with hamburger and cook a long time (1 to 2 hrs.) on low.

title: glinda's sun tea
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Pour water on tea bags in a 1 gallon jar.
Sit mixture in the sun for 1 day or 2 days in a warm kitchen.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: butter roll pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer well.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Let stand at least 20 minutes before serving.
Garnish with a dollop of cool whip and cinnamon.

title: whole wheat bread loaves
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon honey and let set until foamy, 5 to 10 minutes.
Scald milk and remove from heat; stir in remainder of honey, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and beaten eggs to milk.
Stir in 3 cups wheat or graham flour and enough all-purpose flour to make a medium stiff dough.
On a lightly floured surface, knead dough about 10 minutes.
Place in well greased bowl; turn dough to coat surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 60 to 90 minutes.
Punch down and turn out on a lightly floured surface.
Divide in half.
Place in well greased loaf pans.
Let rise again, about 60 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until loaves test done.
Remove from pans.

title: vanilla crisps
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar (or Equal); add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with floured glass.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove immediately from pan.
Makes 72 cookies.

title: cashew hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain grease.
Make sauce by heating mushrooms, olives, cheese, soup, sour cream and cooking sherry in saucepan until cheese melts.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and add all ingredients except chow mein noodles and cashews. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes. The last 10 minutes, top with chow mein noodles and cashews.

title: wasabi salad dressing(seasons 4 small salads)
directions: Mix soy sauce and vinegar in a bowl.
Add sugar and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add sesame oil and wasabi paste and whisk well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
This dressing is suitable for green salad; adjust the amounts of wasabi and sugar depending on your preference.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and almonds into a large 10 x 15 x 2 baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Before baking, spread the cheese and almonds on the top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli and onion until tender.
Do not drain; add salt to taste.
Add canned milk to water and broccoli (enough to make it creamy).
Mix flour with cold water to smooth paste and add to boiling broccoli to make a soup (not thick).
Add cheese to your taste.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to first mixture.
Last, add the junior baby carrots and nuts.
Pour into loaf tin.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shake 'n bake taters
directions: Peel potatoes and quarter them.
Dip potatoes in milk and place in bag with Shake 'n Bake; coat well.
Bake on a cookie sheet that has 1/8-inch oil on it.
Bake approximately for 30 minutes at 400°.
Turn several times.
Can be served with cheese sauce or sour cream.

title: quick raspberry ice cream
directions: Puree raspberries and cream in food processor until soft and creamy. Serve at once or place in plastic container in freezer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook the noodles according to directions.
Brown the ground beef with the onion and drain the grease off of the meat.
Put back in the pan and put the tomato sauce in and add the seasonings and mushrooms.
Let it simmer for 10 to 20 minutes.
When the noodles get done, drain them and put them in a bowl with butter.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Add flour to thicken, roll out and cut into strips;
add to soup while it cooks.

title: chili taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain grease.
Add can of chili, Cheez Whiz and kidney beans.
Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring as needed.
Place prepared ingredients on top of corn chips, lettuce and tomato; top with grated cheese.
Add optional ingredients, if you use (ripe olives and sour cream).

title: cheese cake
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: camp fire punch
directions: The flavor of Kool-Aid determines the color.
One very good "red" is Tropical Fruit.

title: 24 carrot cake
directions: Combine all
ingredients
together.

title: apple cake muffins(yields 12 muffins)
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together eggs, vegetable oil and sugar. Add the almond extract and vanilla.
Fold in the apples and pecans. Sift together the flour, salt, soda and spices.
Add to the liquid mixture and blend just long enough to moisten the dry ingredients. Don't overmix!
Divide the batter among the 12 muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Mix all together in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour until potatoes are tender.
When potatoes are tender, sprinkle 1/2 to 1 cup shredded Colby or Cheddar cheese on top (depending on size of casserole and how much cheese you like).
May use less.
Return casserole to oven until cheese starts to melt.
Serve with warm buns and a green salad or coleslaw.

title: chocolate refrigerator pie
directions: Simmer molasses and shortening for 15 minutes.
In a large bowl, cream sugar, egg and vanilla.
Dissolve soda in hot water. Add soda/water mixture to sugar mixture, then add cloves, cinnamon, salt and ginger.
Beat.
Add molasses mixture, then beat in 6 cups flour.
Roll out dough.
No flour is needed when rolling out dough.
Cut out figures.
Bake 6 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 48 large figures.

title: holiday ribbon ring
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin.
Pour 1 1/2 cups into a 6 cup ring mold.
Chill until set but not firm (15 minutes).
Chill remaining gelatin in bowl.
Gradually blend in 1/3 cup yogurt. Spoon over.
Chill until set but not firm.
Repeat, using lime gelatin.
Chill at least 2 hours before unmolding.

title: meringue
directions: Beat eggs, and cream of tartar adding sugar and vinegar until very stiff.
Put on wax paper and bake at 250 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: eggplant mozzarella
directions: Peel eggplant and slice.
Lay in flat pan and sprinkle with salt.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Pat dry. Dip in flour and brown on both sides in olive oil.
In greased 13 x 9-inch pan, spread bottom with sauce, eggplant and top with cheese. Repeat until full. Top with cheese and Parmesan.
Cover with foil. Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven. Remove foil and bake 10 minutes.

title: prune bread
directions: Pour boiling water over pitted prunes and dissolve the soda in this and let stand for a while.
Mix the shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients to shortening mixture alternately with liquid drained from prunes.
Add 2/3 cup coarsely chopped walnuts and prunes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Let stand overnight before slicing.
Slice very thin and serve with butter.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place mixture in an unbaked pie shell and bake 8 minutes at 400°, then bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Place sliced potatoes in roaster.
Combine onion, milk, cheese, parsley and flour in saucepan.
Cook until cheese melts and
sauce is slightly thickened.
Pour over potatoes.
Add ham cubes.
Stir to mix well.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pinch cake
directions: Melt the first 4 ingredients in boiler; boil 1 minute.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon in bowl.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Cut each biscuit in sixths and coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture (dry mix).
Alternate biscuits in pan with melted mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: parmesan dijon chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs with grated cheese in shallow pan. Combine butter, mustard, Worcestershire, lemon juice and wine. Mix well.
Coat chicken with mixture, then roll in crumbs.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Add lemon wedges.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and bake at 350°, uncovered for 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker pie shell. Refrigerate overnight.

title: meaty spaghetti sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a big pot with no lid.
Simmer several hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes a lot and freezes well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in ungreased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken in a pot-deli style
directions: Cover chicken parts with broth in a 5-quart saucepot.
Add all remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Partially cover, reduce heat to low and simmer about 1 hour, until chicken is very tender, but not yet falling off the bones.
As chicken, cooks, skim fat off surface every 20 minutes. Remove from heat.

title: 45 minute cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, flour and milk.
Mix these well and pour into baking dish containing butter.
Don't stir! Spoon the sweetened fruit into mixture.
Cook 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add milk to desired consistency. Beat until smooth.
Tastes good on a yellow cake in a Bundt pan.

title: rita's crunchy vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers and oleo.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers and oleo.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add eggs gradually and beat until creamy and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Alternate milk and flour.
Start with milk and end with flour.
Add flavoring and mix well.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool Whip may be used if desired as a topping, or may frost with chocolate frosting if preferred.

title: cajun crawfish etouffee
directions: Roux:
Place butter in saucepan and melt.
Stir in flour and cook, stirring, to a golden brown.
Remove from fire and set aside.

title: hershey's chewy cho-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar and brown sugar until well blended. Add eggs and vanilla, beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Gradually add to butter mix beat well.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 - 11 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain.
Cut cheese; cook on medium-low heat.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup; simmer until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add salsa to taste.
Serve warm.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: chicken and mushrooms with wine sauce
directions: On top of stove over medium heat, put butter, onions and garlic in large skillet.
Saute until onions are soft.
Add chicken and broth and cover until chicken is cooked.
Add mushrooms and wine and simmer until soft.
Remove chicken breasts; add thickening to make sauce.
Serve chicken on rice with sauce ladled on top.

title: red bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours.
If it appears to be getting too dry, cover.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese log
directions: Roll softened Velveeta cheese between wax paper into oblong piece.
Spread with cream cheese.
Add green onions, green pepper and pimento.
Roll into a log.
Coat with chopped pecans.
Chill 24 hours.
Serve sliced.

title: purple cow
directions: Mix all ingredients well in blender.
Pour into glass.
Serve.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown meat and
onion in soy sauce.
Add other ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.

title: tortilla turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large skillet, heat the oil. Add the pepper and onion; cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the turkey and cook, stirring as needed, about 5 minutes. Stir in the tomatoes, beans and chilies; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring often, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.

title: drop doughnut holes
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, salt, oil, extract and nutmeg; mix well.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to egg mixture.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon into deep hot fat and fry about 2 1/2 minutes or until brown.
Doughnuts will rise to the surface so continue submerging them to assure even cooking. Drain on paper towel.
Shake with sugar in brown paper bag. Makes about 50.

title: layered vegetable pie
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook mushrooms and shallots with garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add spinach and cook 2 minutes or until liquid has evaporated, stirring constantly.
Stir in flour; set aside.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Spread 1 package of crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and egg yolk together. Spread over the layer of rolls.
Put other package of rolls on top of cream cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and linguine with garlic sauce(4 servings)
directions: In a large pot of boiling, salted water, cook the linguine to desired doneness; drain.
Place in a large serving bowl.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a heavy pan and bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 5 minutes or until it reaches 234° on a candy thermometer. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Let cool at room temperature.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: lemon junk
directions: Cherry pie filling can be used instead of pudding.

title: honey lime dip(for use with fruits)
directions: Mix honey, egg and lime juice and place over low heat until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add sour cream, salt and mace.
Chill until ready to serve.
Place in small bowl and surround with fresh pineapple sticks, strawberries, banana chunks, apples, orange slices, etc.

title: tortilla roll-ups(appetizer)
directions: Spread the cream cheese on tortilla. Drain juice from salsa, then spread layer on top of cream cheese. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Roll up and cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch pieces.

title: italian beef
directions: Put roast in covered roaster and fill halfway with water. Add remaining ingredients. Bake covered at 325° for 4 to 5 hours or in crockpot
until well done and tender.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; spread in a shallow pan.
Spread thin layer liquid taco sauce; top with shredded cheese, lettuce (shredded), tomatoes (cut small), black olives, onion and green peppers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Toss well.
Make a day ahead so that veggies have time to marinate.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil macaroni and drain.
Add 3 eggs to macaroni in pot.
Add 1 teaspoon salt. Add Italian cheese and 1 1/2 teaspoons pepper.
Add 2 tablespoons oil and mix all well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350` for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Top should be a little browned.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread; spread bread slices with butter on each side.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish and set aside.
Spread ham over bread slices; sprinkle with cheese. Combine eggs and half and half;
mix well and pour over cheese. Cover casserole and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake uncovered at 325 - 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Yield 8 servings.

title: lemon freeze
directions: First Mixture:
Mix cornflakes, 2 tablespoons of sugar and melted butter. Save 2 tablespoons for topping.
Then press remaining mixture in pan and chill.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Wash and clean mushrooms with a wire brush, cut in slices and place in a glass dish.
Add pimentos, olives and salad dressing, toss and serve.
Serves 6.

title: rum honey walnut bread
directions: Cream butter with sugar, then add eggs; beat well.
Add honey and stir.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Blend dry ingredients into batter, alternating with rum and water.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well buttered and lightly floured 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: black beans
directions: Coarsely chop bacon, onion and garlic.
In a 12-inch frying pan, over medium heat, stir bacon, onion and garlic until bacon is crisp, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and discard fat.
Drain black beans.
Add beans, chicken stock and vinegar to pan.
Coarsely mash beans with spoon; if made ahead, cover and chill up to one day.
Spoon black beans into an ovenproof dish.
Top beans with corn kernels, then cover with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until hot in the center, about 10 minutes.
Mm mm good.
Gotta try it!

title: reuben casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain sauerkraut and throw out liquid. Mix sauerkraut, sour cream and onions.
Spread into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add layer of corned beef followed by layer of Swiss cheese. Melt margarine and mix with bread crumbs.
Spread bread crumbs over Swiss cheese.
(For bread crumbs, tear slices into pieces and put in your blender - "instant bread crumbs.")
Bake for 45 minutes and serve with dill pickles.

title: evelyn's slaw
directions: Warm oil, vinegar, salt, sugar and mustard over heat until dissolved.
Cool and pour cabbage mixture.
Makes a large amount, especially nice for large dinner party.

title: chewy pecan cookie squares
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar, mayonnaise and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture and 1/2 cup pecans.
(Dough will be thick and sticky.)
Press into well-greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with the remaining pecans and press into dough.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool.
Cookies are soft while hot, but firm when cool.

title: thumb cookies
directions: Mix into small balls.
Mix egg white to froth.
Dip balls into froth.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Take out.
Press thumb in center; then finish baking 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and cream cheese; mix well until well blended.
Blend in eggs, juice and lemon peel.
Add flour and baking powder and mix well.
Chill for several hours.
Shape dough into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly and indent centers.
Fill with preserves.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: taco meat loaf(microwave)
directions: With combination oven-microwave, bake in preheated 350° oven, uncovered 20 to 22 minutes.
An 8-inch round glass or plastic baking dish with a glass in the center can be used in place of ring mold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Form balls, then press down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle cookie with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread 1 can apple pie filling over crust.

title: dutch pea soup
directions: Cover peas with 2 quarts of water and simmer gently for 2 minutes and then let stand for 1 hour.
Add the bone, onion, 1 teaspoon of salt or salt to taste, 1/2 teaspoon pepper, marjoram and the celery and carrots.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer, don't boil, for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally. Remove bone and cut off the meat and dice.
Return the meat to the soup.
Serves 6 to 8.
It tastes even better the next day.

title: chocolate sheet cake icing
directions: Bring to boil the oleo, cocoa and buttermilk.
Remove from heat; add powdered sugar, nuts and vanilla.

title: sweet potato-cashew bake
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in water 20 minutes or until tender. Drain, peel and cut crosswise into thick pieces.
Combine brown sugar, cashews, ginger and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Drain peaches well.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine sliced apples, 3 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Mix together remaining ingredients to make batter. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Put in batter and apples in alternate layers, beginning and ending with batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sunday steak
directions: Brown steak; place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle soup mix over steak.
Add mushrooms on top of soup mix.
Add onion slices, if desired.
Mix gravy and water together and pour over the top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Do not stir.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O and let set to almost firm.
Add remaining ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Makes a large Jell-O salad.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs until hard-boiled.
Cool, shell and then cut in half.
Place egg white on serving plate.
Remove yolks and place in a bowl.
Mix egg yolks, pickle juice, mayonnaise, mustard and all-purpose seasoning together.
Scoop ingredients with a tablespoon into the egg white.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain green beans.
In a large saucepan, combine margarine, flour, salt, pepper, sugar, onions, yogurt and cheese.
Stir and cook over low heat until ingredients are well combined and cheese is melted.
Add beans, mixing well. Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with cornflakes.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a large mixer, cream the cheese 1/3 of package at a time. Mix until creamy.
Add sugar and salt slowly; mix until well blended.
Add 1 egg at a time; mix well after each egg.
Add almond extract.
Pour into spring-form pan with graham cracker crust.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In a large bowl mix milk and whipping cream.
Take out 1 cup and set aside.
Put macaroni in pot with 1 1/2 sticks butter and milk mixture.
Cook on low heat, stirring for 1/2 hour.
When real thick put in buttered 9 x 11-inch Pyrex dish. Sprinkle bottom of dish with Romano cheese.
Pour.
Set aside liquid over macaroni and sprinkle top with Romano cheese.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat slaw
directions: Toss veggies together in a bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, milk, sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over vegetables and toss to coat.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Make pie crust same as for pie, but roll out a little thicker and place in deep casserole dish.
Mix in bowl the soup, vegetables and chicken.
Mix all together and pour in crust. Cover top with crust and bake in oven at 350° until crust is golden brown.
Punch holes in top crust.
You can use cooked roast or leftover for beef pot pie.

title: quick, easy-n-fast snicker snack
directions: Combine cereal, peanuts and raisins in a bowl. Melt butter; pour over cereal mixture and toss until coated. Sprinkle chocolate chips over the mixture and toss again. Pack in small plastic bags for snacks or lunch boxes.

title: crunch-top potatoes
directions: Melt butter in jelly roll pan in moderate oven (375°).
Add single layer of potatoes.
Turn once in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake 1/2 hour or until done and tops are crisp.
Serve hot.

title: english muffins
directions: In a large bowl dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, honey, oil and flour.
Stir until smooth.
On floured surface roll out dough and cut into 3 1/2-inch circles.
Sprinkle cornmeal on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Place the muffins on the sheet and sprinkle with remaining cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in warm spot for about 1 hour.
Heat a griddle.
Transfer muffins onto griddle and cook over the burner for about 7 minutes on each side.
Keep flame low so the muffins don't scorch.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Pour dressing on and mix well.

title: fabulous fudge cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, combine wafer crumbs, sugar and cocoa; stir in butter. Press onto the bottom of a greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Set aside.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and herb seasoned stuffing together well.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Fold in mayonnaise stuffing mixture.
Season to taste.
Refrigerate to allow flavor to blend.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and saute in margarine 10 minutes.
Place a thin layer of onions and mushroom soup on crumbs.
Repeat layers.
Mix milk and eggs together and pour over layers. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add rest of cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chicken-broccoli macaroni bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
In a bowl, stir together the soup and mayonnaise.
Stir in broccoli and lemon juice.
Add cooked macaroni.
Toss to coat well.
Remove chicken from baking dish.
Stir the cooking juices from the baking dish into the macaroni mixture.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with chicken breasts.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over chicken and macaroni.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix Bisquick, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Add beaten eggs. Fold in shredded zucchini.
Fry like small pancakes in hot oil or butter.
